  "GLM_SYSTEMIC_BOTTLENECK_2026_06_20": "KEY FINDING: the credibility-pass member-entailment (z-ai/glm-5.1 via OpenRouter) is SLOW from BOTH boxes — local credibility pass ~49min, VM ~42min+ and STILL in it (stuck at outline, 0 fires). So the assumption 'glm fast on VM' is FALSE right now — it is a SYSTEMIC glm-provider slowness (provider trickle/load), NOT a local-network issue. The VM does NOT meaningfully accelerate the render. CONSEQUENCE: ALL full renders are ~1.5-2.5hr (credibility pass + slow distill_maps + D8 all glm/deepseek-bound). For practical iteration this is UNUSABLE -> a real fix is needed: either (a) find + set the flag that disables the CREDIBILITY-PASS member entailment (PG_STRICT_VERIFY_ENTAILMENT=off did NOT — the credibility pass calls entailment_judge.py directly; need the credibility-specific gate), making the pass deterministic+fast (baskets still form; entailment only verifies membership — for the SURVIVAL/breadth question, deterministic membership suffices), or (b) switch the glm/mirror to a faster provider, or (c) raise PG_CREDIBILITY_PASS_MAX_INFLIGHT for more parallelism. The LOCAL render is currently AHEAD (fired 5/6 enrichment sections = its credibility pass DID complete ~49min; now generating remaining sections, then D8). Take whichever report.md lands first for the SURVIVAL check; the local render is harness-tracked (exit notifies). Do NOT keep per-15min polling (burns context) — rely on the local exit notification + a long fallback. The glm-fix is a likely NEXT build after the survival number (it gates every future render incl the RC-D measurement + cert).",
  "VM_RENDER_LAUNCHED_2026_06_20": "VM render DEPLOYED + LAUNCHED. VM /root/polaris is NOT a git checkout (git rev-parse empty) -> synced via tar(src/polaris_graph + scripts/dr_benchmark + run_honest_sweep_r3.py 6.4MB)->scp->extract; verified_compose.py(16649b, build_short_member_sentence present) + multi_section_generator.py wiring landed + BOTH PARSE on the VM. corpus_snapshot scp'd to /root/polaris/outputs/prc_render_probe/workforce/drb_72_ai_labor/. .env on VM has OPENROUTER+ZYTE keys. LAUNCHED: setsid python -m scripts.dr_benchmark.run_gate_b --only drb_72_ai_labor --resume --out-root outputs/prc_render_probe, same probe env (PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE=1 + PG_STRICT_VERIFY_ENTAILMENT=off + always-release), pid in /root/vm_render.pid, log /root/vm_render.log. GATE-B run live (resuming workforce/drb_72_ai_labor; FA2 competitor-missing warning is non-blocking). VM render is NOT harness-tracked (remote nohup) -> POLL via ssh (ls /root/polaris/outputs/prc_render_probe/workforce/drb_72_ai_labor/report.md + grep vm_render.log). Expected ~25-40min (A15 re-fetch ~15-20min slow on both boxes [network not glm] + credibility pass/D8 FAST on VM glm vs ~49min local). ON report.md: scp it back (or run pack_drb2 on the VM) -> SURVIVAL CHECK: distinct [N] in pack_drb2.answer_body(strip_junk(report.md)) + CONFIRM the verified-compose enrichment-section verbatim sentences + their [N] SURVIVE strip_junk+150K (the advisor gate). Local render (pid 35232, ~100min, fired verified-compose 2x, pre-D8, harness-task bjubikhj9) = parallel FALLBACK (exit notifies). Whichever report.md lands first -> survival check.",
  "ADVISOR_SURVIVAL_GATE_2026_06_20": "Advisor #3: fire is NECESSARY NOT SUFFICIENT. My own forensic history = the 633-sources-rendered-then-EATEN-by-strip_junk+150K case (FORENSIC_RESULT). So the DISCRIMINATING datum is NOT 'verified-compose PRIMARY' (fired) — it is SURVIVAL: do the composed enrichment-section [N] citations actually appear in pack_drb2.answer_body(strip_junk(report.md)) AFTER stripping + 150K truncation? Pure function of report.md, cheap+offline+REAL (the scorer's own truncation). Survive => path proven end-to-end => RC-D. Stripped/truncated out => a render-routing bug RC-D won't fix, comes FIRST. VM CONFIRMED UP (ssh8.vast.ai:39556, /root/polaris present, RTX A6000) — the unchecked-4x critical-path item is SETTLED; VM is the fast-glm vehicle for the full render / RC-D iteration / FINAL cert (local credibility pass ~49min + D8 glm risk make local ~2.5hr/render). PLAN: (1) the local render is harness-tracked (run_in_background bjubikhj9) — STOP per-tick polling; when report.md appears (exit notification) do the SURVIVAL check: python -c 'from scripts.dr_benchmark.pack_drb2 import answer_body,strip_junk; b=answer_body(strip_junk(open(report.md).read())); count distinct [N]; check the enrichment-section verbatim sentences (Background section first-sentences) are IN b'. (2) If the local render HANGS at D8 (glm, like the credibility pass) -> DEPLOY to the VM: push branch bot/I-arch-011-22bug-campaign, VM git fetch+checkout, scp the 2 uncommitted files (verified_compose.py + multi_section_generator.py), ensure corpus_snapshot + .env(keys incl ZYTE) on the VM, run the same resume probe (fast glm ~15min) -> survival check there. DRIVE TO THE SURVIVAL NUMBER — it is the one fact that says whether the wiring earned its keep.",
  "RENDER_PROBE_FIRE_CONFIRMED_2026_06_20": "UNKNOWN #1 RESOLVED: verified-compose FIRES end-to-end through _run_section->render. Proof: '06:19:25 [multi_section] verified-compose PRIMARY: 5 baskets -> draft_chars=1398' (the Background enrichment section; ~280 chars/basket = matches offline 276; credibility_analysis POPULATED not None, so my branch did NOT silently no-op). The short writer + the _run_section elif wiring WORK on the real run path. 150K-FIT: strongly extrapolated (280 chars/basket -> ~535 fit 150K; the rendered 5-basket/1398-char line confirms the per-basket rate) but NOT yet observed in a completed report.md. D8: not yet reached. LOCAL IS IMPRACTICALLY SLOW for a full render: ~88min in + still generating (credibility pass alone ~49min on glm; distill_maps 122-423s each x9 sections; D8 glm pending). The render is PROGRESSING (no hang) but ~2hr/render makes local UNUSABLE for iteration OR cert. CONCLUSION FORMING: local confirms the PATH WIRING; all full renders (150K-fit obs, D8, synthesis-read, RC-D measurement, FINAL cert) move to the campaign VM (glm fast there). Let the local render finish in BACKGROUND (bonus report.md for the 150K-fit + enumeration artifact) but do NOT block on it. The render is ENUMERATION by construction (short writer = single-source per basket, collapsed=0) -> confirms RC-D consolidation + real LLM writer are needed for QUALITY (DeepTRACE penalizes enumeration). verified_compose.py + _run_section wiring + short writer STILL UNCOMMITTED.",
  "RENDER_PROBE_FINDING_2026_06_20_glm_is_credibility_pass": "py-spy on the live probe (pid 35232, ~42min elapsed, $0.23): the run PROGRESSES (A15 re-fetch DONE recovered=32/40; outline built = 3 contract + 6 enrichment sections) and is NOW in run_credibility_analysis -> _assemble_baskets -> _verify_member_in_isolation -> entailment_judge._post_with_total_deadline (credibility_pass.py:361/435). KEY FINDINGS: (1) the LOCAL glm bottleneck is the CREDIBILITY PASS member-entailment (runs INSIDE generation at multi_section_generator.py:7050, BEFORE _run_section + BEFORE D8), NOT D8. (2) PG_STRICT_VERIFY_ENTAILMENT=off did NOT disable it — the credibility pass calls entailment_judge.py DIRECTLY, ungated by that flag (my 'dodge the glm hang' assumption was WRONG). (3) It is PARALLEL now (multiple ThreadPoolExecutor-761 threads = PG_CREDIBILITY_PASS_MAX_INFLIGHT>1 set by the slate) + each call is total-deadline-bounded -> it PROGRESSES (not a hard hang), just slow on local glm (~20min in the pass, wall=PG_CREDIBILITY_PASS_WALL_S=3000s=50min). (4) verified-compose fires for the 6 ENRICHMENT sections via _run_section (contract sections use contract_section_runner, a separate path my wiring does NOT touch) — pending the credibility pass completing. DECISION: let the local render finish (it should clear the pass within the wall -> generation -> verified-compose -> D8 -> render); if it TIMES OUT (credibility degrade -> credibility_analysis=None -> verified-compose no-ops) OR exceeds the wall, that CONFIRMS local is glm-impractical -> move iteration to the campaign VM (glm fast there; deploy uncommitted verified_compose.py + _run_section wiring + short writer). The render PATH is sound; local glm SPEED is the only issue. To force a faster LOCAL credibility pass for future probes: find the flag that disables the credibility-pass member entailment (NOT PG_STRICT_VERIFY_ENTAILMENT) or set PG_CREDIBILITY_PASS_MAX_INFLIGHT higher.",
  "RENDER_PROBE_2026_06_20": "ADVISOR #2 (this session) BLOCKED RC-D again, correctly: get ONE real render BEFORE the multi-day RC-D build (§-1.4 — never stack a big build on a path never run end-to-end). The TIGHTEST unknown reshapes everything: can I render LOCALLY AT ALL? The credibility-pass entailment hung on glm; D8 (release gate) ALSO runs glm -> if D8 hangs the same way, ALL local iteration moves to the VM (changes how I work). The probe tests 3 unknowns FREE: (1) does verified-compose fire through _run_section->render (wiring proof, never confirmed); (2) does short prose fit 150K (observed not modeled); (3) does D8/glm HANG locally (foundational VM-vs-local). BUILT: build_short_member_sentence (verified_compose.py) = DETERMINISTIC no-LLM writer = first sentence of each basket's strongest SUPPORTS member's verified span + its real global token (verbatim prefix -> passes strict_verify + the P1-1 region gate); wired as the _run_section writer_fn (replaces the stub lambda). Offline-proven: avg 276 chars/basket (vs 5157 verbatim, ~19x smaller), 0 fell back to full span, 29 distinct/30 baskets -> at 276 chars ~543 baskets fit 150K. This is a PATH test NOT a quality test (single-source short statements = enumeration, expected/fine here; DeepTRACE-quality needs RC-D consolidation + the real LLM writer). LAUNCHED (bg, harness-tracked): run_gate_b --only drb_72_ai_labor --resume --out-root outputs/prc_render_probe with PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE=1 + PG_STRICT_VERIFY_ENTAILMENT=off (dodges the credibility-pass glm hang; deepseek gen works locally) + always-release; D8 STAYS ON (that's unknown #3). log=outputs/prc_render_probe/render_probe.log. WATCH: grep 'verified-compose PRIMARY' (fire), report.md (complete+150K-fit), D8/glm ssl.recv hang (-> VM). ON COMPLETE: count distinct [N] in pack_drb2.answer_body + §-1.1 synthesis-vs-enumeration read. ON D8 HANG: the finding = iterate on VM. Two build flags for RC-D later (advisor): per-basket LLM writer is O(684) calls = serial-hang risk -> consider per-SECTION (basket claims as structured input to ONE call); NLI/embedding lethal failure = merging similar-but-OPPOSITE claims ('AI reduces jobs'~'AI increases jobs' high cosine opposite meaning) -> NEGATIVE test MUST include reduces-vs-increases pairs. verified_compose.py + multi_section_generator.py wiring + short writer STAY UNCOMMITTED (probe).",
  "ADVISOR_REFRAME_2026_06_20_RCD_IS_PREREQUISITE": "BLOCKING verdict on the 654 signal: INCONCLUSIVE, do NOT commit PR-c or declare breadth moved. The 684-baskets-from-684-sources = collapsed=0 = ZERO consolidation = pure per-source ENUMERATION (the oversized dump strip_junk+150K already kill; my ~29-rendered math lands in the no-move 18-40 band). I compared a real-pipeline number (baseline 20, on 825->412 consolidated) against a DEGENERATE-pipeline number (654: judge=None+entailment-off bypassed consolidation, stub writer, no render) — NOT comparable. THE WINNING DESIGN is NOT one verbatim span/source x684; it is CONSOLIDATED multi-member baskets, each rendered as ONE SYNTHESIZED statement citing ALL its members (the inline corroborator surface that test-fires) -> N baskets x k members = many sources, FEW statements = breadth WITH synthesis. collapsed=0 is the worst case (1 source/statement -> 150K overflow). SO: (1) RC-D (collapsed>0, multi-member baskets) is a PREREQUISITE for measuring PR-c, NOT a follow-on — cannot validate verified-compose on an unconsolidated corpus; if RC-D isn't built, RC-D IS the real first build (not PR-c-with-stub). (2) The dump trap is a BLOCKING design concern not a render detail: distinct-[N] is a PROXY; high [N] from per-source enumeration is a LOSS (DeepTRACE penalizes one-sided enumeration; my own auto_reject_traps calls packer-gaming auto-reject) -> the gate MUST be distinct-[N] AND a §-1.1 synthesis-vs-enumeration read. (3) STOP offline-proxying (every offline config has a fatal gap: entailment-off changes membership, judge=None kills consolidation, stub!=real writer, no truncation) — it is a RENDER question. CONCRETE ORDER: [A] RC-D consolidation (collapsed>0) — the real first build (#1274, DECISION 3 two-op: numeric safety key UNTOUCHED + additive qualitative semantic clustering, exact-or-singleton over-merge guard + NEGATIVE case, behavioral collapsed>0 on drb_72). [B] PR-c REAL abstractive writer (short synthesized prose per basket citing ALL members, prompt-constrained to the basket's claim — the stub only ever measured a dump; this was always the actual PR-c). [C] REAL render (local entailment-off+always-release+real deepseek writer = fast NON-CERT signal since deepseek works locally / glm only blocks entailment+D8; VM = cert) -> measure rendered distinct-[N] AND read synthesis-vs-enumeration. Modest consolidation (~2:1) + short synthesis fits ~400 multi-cite statements in 150K = genuine breadth move. The _run_section stub-writer wiring + verified_compose.py + harness STAY UNCOMMITTED; the real writer replaces the stub; do NOT commit PR-c on the 654.",
  "BREADTH_SIGNAL_2026_06_20": "MEASURED (fast offline, credibility pass entailment=off to dodge the LOCAL glm-mirror entailment-socket hang that wedged the run_gate_b resume; deepseek gen works locally, glm trickles -> the I-arch-007 hang class, credibility per-member verify is SERIAL by design PG_CREDIBILITY_PASS_MAX_INFLIGHT=1 gated behind an undone thread-safety fix). RESULT on drb_72 (684 deduped sources): verified-compose-primary composed 684 baskets -> 654 DISTINCT sources cited (30 insufficient-ev stubs) vs the 20-source baseline. MECHANISM CONFIRMED >>40: composing ALL section baskets reaches ~all sources. BUT THE CRITICAL NUANCE (advisor predicted this exact failure, warning #4): the STUB writer emits each basket's VERBATIM K-span = avg 5157 chars/basket -> 3,527,603 total chars -> the 150K pack_drb2.answer_body scorer budget keeps only ~29 baskets -> rendered scored breadth would be ~29, NOT 654. The verbatim path RECREATES the oversized-dump problem (same as 'Corroborated Weighted Findings' that strip_junk+150K discards). THEREFORE: the verbatim fallback is a per-basket SAFETY NET (rare, on compose-fail), NOT the primary output; the breadth payoff REQUIRES the REAL ABSTRACTIVE writer (short 1-2 sentence synthesis per basket ~200-400 chars, prompt-constrained to the basket's claim) so ~400-600 baskets fit in 150K. Also collapsed=0 here (684 singletons) because the offline judge=None+entailment-off pass didn't consolidate; the real run's RC-D consolidation makes MULTI-member baskets (fewer baskets, each multi-cite) which changes the truncation math favorably. NEXT (advisor-consulted): build/finalize the REAL abstractive per-basket writer (deepseek short prose, the working local provider) -> measure rendered distinct-[N] with IT (not the stub) -> that is the true PR-c gate. The §-1.4 fires-in-real-output cert stays the FINAL VM run (clean glm).",
  "WIRE_AND_MEASURE_LAUNCH_2026_06_20": "BINDING action #1 DONE: verified-compose-primary WIRED into _run_section (multi_section_generator.py:3909) as an `elif` between the FIX-K enrichment branch and the legacy `_call_section` else — fires when `_verified_compose_enabled()` AND credibility_analysis is not None AND `_section_baskets_for_compose(section, credibility_analysis)` non-empty: raw='\\n'.join(_compose_section_per_basket(baskets, evidence_pool, writer_fn=STUB (lambda:'' -> verbatim K-span per basket, NO LLM for the breadth lower-bound), verify_fn=verify_sentence_provenance)) -> flows through the UNCHANGED _rewrite_draft_with_spans + strict_verify(:3942) -> resolve. Flag-OFF / empty baskets / credibility None -> legacy _call_section byte-identical. Parses+imports clean. CANONICAL DE-RISK (advisor caught: the row collision, not the method): my first OFFLINE run_credibility_analysis on raw evidence_for_gen hit `weight_mass origin::ev_642 found 2 canonical rows` -> would DEGRADE to credibility_analysis=None under always-release -> my branch would SILENTLY NO-OP (advisor's exact warning). ROOT CAUSE: production passes list(evidence_pool.values()) = DEDUPED-BY-ID (multi_section_generator.py:7053), not the raw list (749 raw -> 684 deduped, 65 dup ids). Deduped, the pass gets PAST the canonical check (both offline attempts then ran the SLOW priors-only loop >5min, no canonical error) -> production WON'T degrade -> my branch WILL fire. BINDING action #2 LAUNCHED: local run_gate_b --only drb_72_ai_labor --resume --out-root outputs/prc_measure with PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE=1 + the sovereign env (deepseek/glm/minimax/qwen via OpenRouter, PG_ALWAYS_RELEASE=1, PG_CREDIBILITY_PASS_WALL_S=3000) -> log outputs/prc_measure/resume_verified_compose.log (BEHAVIORAL_CANARY_OK, resuming). MEASUREMENT = grep the log for `verified-compose PRIMARY: N baskets` (the §-1.4 fired-in-output proof) + count distinct [N] in pack_drb2.answer_body(strip_junk(outputs/prc_measure/workforce/drb_72_ai_labor/report.md)). >40 => verified-compose MOVES breadth (PRIMARY confirmed) -> finalize cross-claim rule via writer-prompt-constraint WITH data, Codex-gate, commit PR-c. ~18-40 => contract-slot bound intact -> fix THAT. ALSO §-1.1 scan the rendered output for an ACTUAL cross-claim mis-citation. Offline _compose count is NOT the measurement (advisor: must fire through _run_section->render); the resume render IS.",
  "ADVISOR_REDIRECT_2026_06_20_STOP_POLISHING_MEASURE": "Advisor (this session) HARD redirect after 5 Codex rounds on the verified-compose CORE: STOP perfecting cross-claim faithfulness of code that is (a) NOT wired into _run_section (Codex flags every round) and (b) whose breadth payoff is UNMEASURED (distinct-[N] still 40). The exactly-one-cluster PIVOT is likely DISQUALIFYING: multi-cluster sources ARE the corroboration §-1.3 wants -> excluding them DELETES the breadth this PR exists to create. Decide the cross-claim mechanism with REAL DATA, not in a vacuum; cross-claim drift (if real on the live path) is better handled by constraining the WRITER to the basket's claim (the prompt) than by a pool exclusion. COMMIT NEITHER the current region-check core (known hole) NOR the pivot yet. BINDING NEXT ACTIONS (both on drb_72 corpus_snapshot, offline/flag-scoped, nothing ships): (1) DATA, no code: of drb_72's consolidated baskets, what fraction of members are single-cluster vs multi-cluster? most multi-cluster => exactly-one-cluster rule is self-defeating. (2) KEYSTONE: wire verified-compose as PRIMARY in the WORKING TREE (uncommitted, PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE=1 for the replay only), run drb_72 (resume from corpus_snapshot, no re-retrieval), count distinct [N] in pack_drb2.answer_body(strip_junk(report.md)). >40 => it MOVES breadth -> finalize the cross-claim rule WITH the data -> commit. ~18-40 => it does NOT deliver primary -> fix THAT (the contract-slot bound) before any more faithfulness rounds. ALSO §-1.1 scan the rendered output for an ACTUAL cross-claim mis-citation (does the leak Codex theorizes even occur with the real writer?). NEXT TICK = do these two measurements; the current verified_compose.py (region-check, uncommitted) is usable AS-IS to PRODUCE output for the measurement (cross-claim correctness finalized AFTER, with data).",
  "PRC_BUILD_STATE_2026_06_20": "ADVISOR (this session) on PR-c: build verified-compose as the PRIMARY section-prose producer (compose ALL of a section's baskets; contract entities are a SUBSET) — augment leaves the 18-source contract-slot bound intact. KEYSTONE CHECK = a CHEAP drb_72 banked-corpus replay AFTER PR-c: distinct cited [N] in pack_drb2.answer_body must exceed the run7 baseline of 40 (a green component harness != the assembled report cites more). Encode the design fixtures verbatim (I wrote both harness+production -> self-confirm risk); Codex brief asks 'does the harness test the contract'. PART A (CORE) DONE: new src/polaris_graph/generator/verified_compose.py (_verified_compose_enabled / split_into_sentences / build_verified_span_draft [basket's strongest SUPPORTS member verbatim direct_quote + its own [#ev:] token] / _basket_scoped_pool [P1-2 enforcement] / _compose_one_basket [writer->strict_verify scoped->keep or fall back to OWN K-span->never empty] / _compose_section_per_basket [PRIMARY, ALL baskets] / _section_baskets_for_compose [ALL baskets whose member ev_ids intersect the section's assigned ev_ids]) + re-exported from multi_section_generator.py + a FRESH fail-loud harness scripts/iarch011_prc_verified_compose_replay_harness.py (3 fixtures c1-fail->own-K-span/c2-pass/c3-FOREIGN[#ev:c2]->reject-under-basket-scoped-pool->own-K-span). PASSES with the REAL strict_verify. Core iter1 gate CAUGHT 2 REAL faithfulness P1s -> FIXED: (P1-1 cross-claim via SHARED source) _basket_scoped_pool now pins each scoped row to the MEMBER'S OWN claim-specific direct_quote (overriding direct_quote+statement), NOT the global evidence_pool row -> a shared source backing another basket's claim can't span-ground here (cluster_id_by_evidence is 1-to-many); +harness shared-id case proving basket C rejects B's claim via the shared id -> C's own span. (P1-2 dropped re-anchored sentence) _compose_one_basket now appends res.sentence (the verifier's re-pointed final_sentence after PG_SPAN_RESOLVER), not the raw input. Hardened harness PASSES. iter2 gate confirmed those 2 fixes (P2) but caught 2 NEW P1s about downstream TOKEN ANCHORING -> FIXED: (P1-3 fallback token mis-anchored downstream) verify now uses the GLOBAL evidence_pool rows (offsets stay global), the verbatim fallback emits the member's REAL global span offsets [#ev:eid:span0-span1] (not 0-len), + the harness adds a GLOBAL RE-VERIFY of every emitted sentence vs the downstream pool. (P1-4 multi-sentence span single token) build_verified_span_draft splits the span into PER-SENTENCE units each tagged with the member's span token. P1-1 re-enforced via a POST-VERIFY REGION CHECK (_tokens_within_basket_regions): a sentence passes only if strict_verify passes AND every token's offsets fall WITHIN this basket's member span regions (a shared source's other-claim span span-grounds globally but is outside this basket's region -> rejected). Harness now models the shared source as a global full text + per-member offsets. iter3 (cap) gate caught a REAL PRODUCTION FAITHFULNESS BLOCKER (not cap-shipped per §-1.2 #6): the region check relied on BasketMember.span being global offsets, but _assemble_baskets (credibility_pass.py:691) sets span=(0,len(span_text)) LOCAL -> region check vacuous in production. FIXED: new _member_global_span(member, evidence_pool) recovers the REAL global region by LOCATING the member's direct_quote inside the global evidence_pool[eid] row (haystack.find), fail-closed if absent; _basket_member_regions + build_verified_span_draft now use it. Production-shape sanity confirmed: member.span=(0,30) local but recovered global region=(34,64). Harness PASSES. iter4 (past cap-3, justified = real faithfulness blocker) gate RUNNING (b5sqf7qfw, event-driven). ON APPROVE commit (git add src/polaris_graph/generator/verified_compose.py src/polaris_graph/generator/multi_section_generator.py scripts/iarch011_prc_verified_compose_replay_harness.py) ref #1268. FAITHFULNESS CHAIN now complete: scoped global pool + post-verify region check (recovered global member regions) + global-anchored per-sentence fallback + re-anchored res.sentence + harness global-re-verify; strict_verify UNCHANGED. iter2/3 P2: reachability core-only -> Part B PRIMARY wiring is the IMMEDIATE next step. iter4 gate (b5sqf7qfw) REQUEST_CHANGES 2 MORE P1s -> DEEP INSIGHT: (P1-A) regions must be SUPPORTS-only (was all members). (P1-B) the REGION approach is FUNDAMENTALLY UNSOUND: _assemble_baskets sets direct_quote=_row_span_text(row)=row.direct_quote (credibility_pass.py:669,692) = the WHOLE evidence row, SAME for all claims of a source -> the recovered region is always the whole row -> CANNOT distinguish claims of the same source -> same-source cross-claim drift survives. PIVOT (the PROVEN fix, mirrors verified_corroborators_for_tokens's anti-cross-claim rule): a member is compose-eligible iff span_verdict==SUPPORTS AND cluster_id_by_evidence[eid] maps to EXACTLY this one cluster (basket.claim_cluster_id); a shared/multi-cluster source is AMBIGUOUS -> EXCLUDED. Enforce by SCOPING the verify pool to eligible members only (a foreign/shared/UNSUPPORTED token is then absent -> fails closed); REMOVE the fragile region/offset gymnastics. cluster_id_by_evidence is available (credibility_pass.py:934-951, in CredibilityAnalysis). Requires threading cluster_id_by_evidence into _compose_section_per_basket/_compose_one_basket/build_verified_span_draft + the harness constructing it (shared case: cluster_id_by_evidence[ev_shared]=[b,c] -> ineligible -> c_shared renders insufficient-evidence disclosure, the conservative correct outcome). ADVISOR-CONSULTED the pivot. iter5 = implement the exactly-one-cluster pool-scoping redesign + re-gate. (Going past cap-3 is justified: real faithfulness blocker, §-1.2 #6.) PART B (PRIMARY WIRING) NEXT: integration point = _run_section (multi_section_generator.py:3799; legacy LLM draft _call_section at :3911 -> strict_verify at :3942 -> kept_sentences). When _verified_compose_enabled() AND _section_baskets_for_compose(section, credibility_analysis) non-empty: produce the section draft via _compose_section_per_basket(baskets, evidence_pool, writer_fn=<per-basket generator-role call, bounded-parallel, reuse _call_section's LLM scoped to the basket's spans>, verify_fn=verify_sentence_provenance) -> raw='\n'.join(composed) -> flows through the EXISTING strict_verify->resolve (idempotent re-verify; P1-2 already enforced internally before the draft). Empty baskets/flag-off -> legacy _call_section byte-identical. WRITER GRANULARITY = a design decision (per-basket N calls vs batched); bounded parallelism + wall to avoid the I-arch-007 serial-LLM hang. THEN the drb_72 replay (keystone). ADVISOR-CONSULT the wiring mechanics before authoring Part B.",
  "RELAND_COMPLETE_2026_06_20": "ALL 6 composition-redesign PRs re-landed into HEAD: PR-a 94494daf (STORM scaffold proof#1), 010-PR1a 1063e6e9 (member_tier seam + judge_error->advisory + a caught faithfulness-leak fix), PR-b 4f5223db (corroboration render proof#2 render-half), PR-d b9b4b5ca (abstract/conclusion), PR-e 3a56b561 (orchestrator harness), PR-f 0e8724a8 (Gate-B slate force-on the 4 composition flags). GH #1268 updated. NOW THE 2 NEW BUILDS (delicate): PR-c verified-compose production + RC-D qualitative consolidation, then FINAL VM run. PR-c HARNESS NOTE: scripts/iarch011_prc_verified_compose_replay_harness.py CANNOT be regenerated from codex_diff_prc.patch (it is a MODIFY-diff and the untracked base file was rm'd during cleanup) -> WRITE the harness FRESH from composition_design_plan.md + the patch's assertions (the contract: per-basket abstractive prose via the existing generator-role path -> deterministic strict_verify each sentence -> FALL BACK to THAT BASKET'S OWN verified K-span [build_verified_span_draft = source's own verbatim quote words; basket-id-bound] else insufficient-evidence disclosure, NEVER empty; P1-2: a sentence citing another basket's ev_id is REJECTED under the basket-scoped pool -> own K-span; assertion uses c1 FORCE-FAIL->K-span / c2 PASS / c3 FOREIGN-cite->reject->own-K-span). Then BUILD _compose_section_per_basket + build_verified_span_draft in src/polaris_graph/generator/multi_section_generator.py to satisfy it. LLM ORGANIZES verified spans, cannot fabricate; strict_verify UNCHANGED. ADVISOR-CONSULT before authoring PR-c (and RC-D) — they are crown-jewel-adjacent.",
  "RELAND_PLAN_2026_06_20": "#1268 = 6 PRs, Codex-audited 2026-06-18, NEVER merged, shared files (run_honest_sweep_r3.py/run_gate_b.py) DRIFTED under the bug-fix campaign so PRB/PRC/PRF git-apply-CONFLICT (PRA/PRD/PRE apply clean). Diffs+verdicts in .codex/I-arch-011/codex_diff_pr{a..f}.patch. Re-land PR-by-PR via the disciplined cycle (apply/re-author -> offline smoke -> Codex re-gate run_in_background -> commit). VERDICTS: pra=APPROVE(v2) prb=APPROVE prc=APPROVE prd=APPROVE(iter3) pre=APPROVE pre2 prf=APPROVE. MAP to wiring proofs: PRA=STORM-outline sections (proof#1, scored-breadth lever); PRB=corroboration RENDER (proof#2 render-half; appends AFTER ##Bibliography=appendix disclosure, §-1.3 honesty, NOT the scored region); PRC=verified-compose w/ basket-id verbatim fallback (proof#3, scored prose); PRD=abstract/exec-summary/conclusion-last; PRE=composition replay harness; PRF=run_gate_b slate wiring. SCORED-BREADTH levers = PRA(widen narrative)+RC-D(multi-member baskets->inline multi-cite via the already-wired surface)+PRC(verified-compose). PROOF#2 needs BOTH PRB(render) AND RC-D/consolidation(collapsed>0); PRB alone renders run7's singletons (no change). FAITHFULNESS-LOCKED per composition_design_plan.md: basketing DETERMINISTIC (reuse finding_dedup/embedding+existing strict_verify for labels, NO new LLM); compose's ONLY new LLM = the abstractive writer via the EXISTING generator-role path (no new model/slug); strict_verify UNCHANGED; verbatim fallback = basket-id-bound (failed sentence falls back to ITS OWN basket K-span only, Codex P1-2). Each PR ships its fail-loud replay harness; FINAL gate = ONE fresh VM run §-1.1-audited.",
  "RELAND_PROGRESS": "PR-a COMMITTED 94494daf (STORM-outline proof#1; re-gate caught + I fixed a real partial_mode drift P1; iter2 APPROVE; 24 tests green). DEPENDENCY DISCOVERED: I-arch-011 PR-b (corroboration render) CONSUMES the I-arch-010 (#1267) member_tier seam (MEMBER_TIER_ENTAILMENT_VERIFIED/DETERMINISTIC_ONLY/UNVERIFIED + BasketMember.member_tier), which is ALSO unmerged. So the re-land is INTERDEPENDENT: I-arch-010 PR1a is a PREREQUISITE for PR-b. REVISED ORDER: PR-a(done 94494daf) -> 010-PR1a(member_tier seam + FIX-1 judge_error->advisory) -> 011-PR-b -> RC-D -> 011-PR-c -> 011-PR-d -> 011-PR-e -> 011-PR-f -> final VM run. 010-PR1a re-landed against drifted HEAD: production seam applied clean (offsets); the FIX-1 test rename/split in test_verification_mode_phase0b.py was re-authored by hand (legacy hard-drop pinned to kill-switch PG_ENTAILMENT_JUDGE_ERROR_ADVISORY=0 + new advisory-keep-default test); 37 tests + the no-leak harness (DETERMINISTIC_ONLY/UNVERIFIED never counted as support; only ENTAILMENT_VERIFIED counted; genuine entailment-fail still drops) GREEN. 010-PR1a gate RUNNING (bfnr51p1v, event-driven). ON APPROVE: commit 010-PR1a files (credibility_pass.py provenance_generator.py multi_section_generator.py test_verification_mode_phase0b.py test_provenance_reanchor.py scripts/iarch010_replay_breadth_faithfulness_harness.py) ref #1267 -> then re-land 011-PR-b (apply --reject: production+harness land clean, only the test append rejects -> extract the +lines + append; PR-b consumes member_tier which now exists) -> smoke -> gate -> commit. FAITHFULNESS: FIX-1 judge_error->advisory = operator-locked always-release (LABEL weak, never silently drop); no-leak guard in the tier classifier (harness-proven); strict_verify floor unchanged. 010-PR1a iter1 re-gate CAUGHT A REAL FAITHFULNESS LEAK the original APPROVE missed (my sharper brief surfaced it): a genuine NEUTRAL/CONTRADICTED first verdict -> local-window rescue -> rescue-call judge_error was treated as non-failing + advisory-kept -> is_verified=True (laundering a genuine entailment failure). FIXED at provenance_generator.py ~2196: the rescue-result branch is now if/elif/else — a rescue-call judge_error FAILS CLOSED on the ORIGINAL genuine verdict (reason rescue_judge_error_on_genuine_{verdict}, does NOT set judge_error_flag); only the PRIMARY judge_error (no prior genuine verdict) advisory-keeps. +test_s0b4_rescue_judge_error_after_genuine_neutral_fails_closed (NUMERIC fixture, NEUTRAL-then-judge_error double, asserts is_verified=False). 38 tests + no-leak harness green. 010-PR1a iter2 APPROVE -> COMMITTED 1063e6e9 (member_tier seam now in HEAD). 011-PR-b RE-LANDED: applied COMPLETELY clean (010-PR1a's commit settled line numbers); 8 PR-b tests + the corroboration-render replay harness GREEN — harness proves it FIRES in REAL rendered output: COUNT='2 verified independent sources' (verified_support_origin_count NOT 4 members), per-source weights, CONTRADICTED label, DETERMINISTIC_ONLY grounded-but-weak disclosure, NO inflation (weak never on SUPPORT line, UNVERIFIED never surfaced). PR-b gate RUNNING (bljpjz91u, event-driven). ON APPROVE: commit PR-b (scripts/run_honest_sweep_r3.py scripts/iarch011_prb_corroboration_replay_harness.py tests/polaris_graph/blockers/test_g2_runsweep_blockers.py) ref #1268/#1275 -> then RC-D (qualitative consolidation = proof#2 collapsed>0 feeder; the SYNTHESIS files finding_dedup/claim_graph/credibility_pass, disjoint from PR-b; DECISION 3 two-op fail-closed; the MOST faithfulness-sensitive build -> commit PR-b first with a clean tree, do NOT start RC-D until PR-b commits). Then PR-c -> PR-d -> PR-e -> PR-f -> final VM run. RE-LAND TALLY: PR-a 94494daf, 010-PR1a 1063e6e9 (caught+fixed a real faithfulness leak), PR-b 4f5223db (APPROVE). GH #1268 updated. PR-c FINDING: the verified-compose PRODUCTION (_compose_section_per_basket + build_verified_span_draft) does NOT exist anywhere in src (only referenced in comments + the existing harness import) — so PR-c is a genuine NEW BUILD (proof #3), NOT a re-land; only its harness scripts/iarch011_prc_verified_compose_replay_harness.py exists and IS the acceptance SPEC (encodes the faithfulness contract: compose abstractive prose per basket -> strict_verify each sentence -> FALL BACK to THAT BASKET'S OWN verified K-span on failure [basket-id-bound, Codex P1-2], + the P1-2 basket-scoped FOREIGN-CITATION rejection: a sentence citing another basket's ev_id must be rejected under the basket-scoped pool -> own K-span). REVISED REMAINING (re-order: cheap re-lands first, then the 2 new builds): PR-d (re-land abstract_conclusion.py, APPROVE patch) -> PR-e (re-land composition replay harness) -> PR-f (re-land run_gate_b slate) -> PR-c (BUILD verified-compose production to satisfy the harness-as-spec + design: _compose_section_per_basket via the EXISTING generator-role path, build_verified_span_draft = the source's own verbatim quote words; LLM ORGANIZES verified spans, cannot fabricate; faithfulness via the UNCHANGED strict_verify) -> RC-D (BUILD qualitative consolidation, #1274) -> FINAL fresh VM run. Note PG_BASKET_CONSUME_FINDING_DEDUP already =1 in the slate; RENDER_VERIFIED_SPANS production already in HEAD (5 matches) but is the enrichment-dump span render, NOT _compose_section_per_basket. PR-d RE-LANDED: applied clean (abstract_conclusion.py new file + run_honest_sweep_r3.py wiring + harness); harness PASS (empty-body->disclosed not fabricated, flag-OFF byte-identical, P2-2 redaction-dup, faithfulness untouched). PR-d gate RUNNING (bubfxsmf8, event-driven). ON APPROVE commit (git add scripts/run_honest_sweep_r3.py src/polaris_graph/generator/abstract_conclusion.py scripts/iarch011_prd_abstract_conclusion_replay_harness.py) ref #1268. NOTE: scripts/iarch011_prc_verified_compose_replay_harness.py is UNTRACKED (a prior-session leftover, NOT in HEAD) — it is PR-c's harness/spec; when building PR-c, regenerate it cleanly from codex_diff_prc.patch + BUILD _compose_section_per_basket + build_verified_span_draft. PR-d COMMITTED b9b4b5ca (APPROVE). PR-e RE-LANDED: applied clean (scripts/iarch011_composition_replay_harness.py, orchestrator; runs the per-component harnesses + discloses not-locally-replayable parts; rc=0); gate RUNNING (b7nvgexbg, event-driven). ON APPROVE commit (git add scripts/iarch011_composition_replay_harness.py) ref #1268. REVISED REMAINING after PR-e: PR-f (re-land run_gate_b slate, codex_diff_prf.patch, +34) -> PR-c (BUILD verified-compose production _compose_section_per_basket+build_verified_span_draft, harness-as-spec) -> RC-D (BUILD qualitative consolidation #1274) -> FINAL fresh VM run. RE-LAND TALLY: PR-a 94494daf, 010-PR1a 1063e6e9, PR-b 4f5223db, PR-d b9b4b5ca, PR-e 3a56b561 DONE. PR-f RE-AUTHORED (2 of 3 hunks rejected/drifted -> re-authored by hand: the 4 composition flags PG_STORM_OUTLINE_SECTIONS/PG_BASKET_CORROBORATION_RENDER/PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE/PG_SYNTHESIS_ABSTRACT_CONCLUSION added to _FULL_CAPABILITY_BENCHMARK_SLATE + _BENCHMARK_FORCE_ON_FLAGS; hunk#2 preflight-required landed clean); each flag 3x; run_gate_b parses+imports clean. PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE pinned AHEAD of PR-c production (no run between -> inert, safe; flagged to Codex). PR-f gate RUNNING (byyz09ork, event-driven). ON APPROVE commit (git add scripts/dr_benchmark/run_gate_b.py) ref #1268 -> RE-LAND of #1268/#1267 existing PRs COMPLETE. THEN the 2 NEW BUILDS (delicate): PR-c BUILD verified-compose production (_compose_section_per_basket + build_verified_span_draft, harness scripts/iarch011_prc_verified_compose_replay_harness.py [untracked] is the SPEC; regenerate cleanly from codex_diff_prc.patch; compose via existing generator-role path, basket-id-bound verbatim K-span fallback, P1-2 foreign-cite reject; LLM organizes verified spans cannot fabricate; strict_verify UNCHANGED) -> RC-D BUILD qualitative consolidation #1274 (DECISION 3 two-op, Op-1 numeric safety key UNTOUCHED + Op-2 additive qualitative semantic clustering, exact-or-singleton over-merge guard + NEGATIVE case, behavioral collapsed>0 on drb_72) -> FINAL fresh VM run §-1.1-audited. Advisor-consult before authoring PR-c/RC-D if unsure.",
  "DECISIVE_TEST_RESOLVED_2026_06_20": "ANSWERED WITH A FACT (not inference). The advisor-mandated injected-basket test ALREADY EXISTS + PASSES on current HEAD: tests/polaris_graph/generator/test_breadth_corroborator_faithfulness_iarch007.py::test_contract_path_supports_member_absent_from_pool_never_surfaces drives the REAL run_contract_section with a 3-member ClaimBasket and asserts the in-pool corroborator renders inline ([n2] in the section body) -> 6 passed. So the SCORED contract-narrative path's inline corroborator surface is WIRED + FIRES (commit a8b6ea3f #1257; contract_section_runner.py:1276-1280 threads baskets, :1364-1372 appends same-cluster SUPPORTS via verified_corroborators_for_tokens). CONCLUSION: RC-D multi-member baskets WOULD surface inline multi-cite in the scored region = NOT a no-op; 'render-routing' is ALREADY WIRED, NOT a module to build; the forensic critic was WRONG on RC-D-no-ops/render-routing-first (its generation hop FAILED -> bad reconstruction). CONFIRMED FIX ORDER: 1) generation-breadth keystone (widen the 18-claim scored narrative to cite MANY claims) 2) RC-D complementary (multi-member baskets -> corroboration-per-cited-claim, the existing surface surfaces them) ; both feed the existing inline surface; 633 dump shrinks as breadth moves inline. SCOPED-OUT per the test docstring + Codex scope-lock (contract_section_runner.py:386-397): attaching DIFFERENT-cluster/non-contract sources as corroborators is OUT (anti-cross-claim §-1.1 lethal); the hard contract-entity wall is at contract_section_runner.py:963-966 — THE generation-breadth lever (why only contract-entity claims render = narrow narrative).",
  "ADVISOR_MANDATED_NEXT_ACTION_2026_06_20": "BEFORE authoring RC-D or gen-breadth: build a behavioral test that INJECTS one synthetic multi-member basket (a claim cluster with 2-3 SUPPORTS members + matching cluster_id_by_evidence) and renders through the ACTUAL contract-slot path that produced the 13K/18-source scored narrative (NOT verified_corroborators_for_tokens in isolation), then asserts a >=2-citation sentence SURVIVES into pack_drb2.answer_body(strip_junk(report)). This ends the wired-vs-FIRED question with a FACT (run7 cannot disambiguate: 0 baskets exercised nothing). OUTCOMES: (a) multi-cite emits -> inline scored surface works -> build RC-D + gen-breadth, NO render-routing module needed; (b) no multi-cite -> the SCORED-narrative call-site passes baskets=None / B6/B8 off -> that narrow wiring fix IS render-routing, comes FIRST. Either way gen-breadth stays keystone, RC-D complementary, NEVER ship RC-D alone. The test is the reusable keystone acceptance harness, not throwaway. Loci to identify: which of multi_section_generator.py:4033-4041 vs :7363-7380 renders the scored Key-Findings narrative (the 13K/18-source region), vs the enrichment dump path near :6914-6960.",
  "active_step": "INVESTIGATION COMPLETE — keystone fully diagnosed. THE KEYSTONE (#1275 generation-breadth) = WIRE/MERGE the OPEN #1268 composition redesign so its 3 FULLY-WIRED proofs FIRE in the rendered output. #1268's COMPOSE-layer (STORM-outline section routing + Argus consolidate-keep-all + verified-compose w/ verbatim fallback) is DESIGNED + Codex-audited (PRA-PRD in .codex/I-arch-011/) but NOT MERGED into HEAD (recent commits are all bug-fixes: FIX-P0-A1/B/C1, collapse F2-F5, judge; NO composition-redesign COMPOSE commits). run7 = the legacy template: 18-slot contract narrative + collapsed=0 single-cite + 633 unbound dumped = the EXACT 'NOT wired' failure in state/iarch_wiring_acceptance_checklist.md. ACCEPTANCE (operator-locked 2026-06-18, the FULLY-WIRED gate): (1) STORM-outline section routing fired (not legacy 18-slot contract template) -> widens the narrative beyond the N-entity contract wall (contract_section_runner.py:963-966); (2) baskets consolidated+multi-source collapsed>0 (RC-D feeds this); (3) verified-compose fired w/ verbatim fallback (failed sentence -> verbatim not empty). Each PR ships a fail-loud behavioral replay on a real corpus_snapshot; FINAL gate = ONE fresh VM run §-1.1-audited. NEXT TICK: locate #1268 PRA-PRD designs/diffs (.codex/I-arch-011/ + the design workflow wer2qbdza + state/iarch010_tail_redesign_scope.md Half-B) -> determine built-vs-unmerged per PR -> WIRE them into the run path (multi_section_generator/contract_section_runner -> STORM-outline adapter) via the disciplined cycle (issue->grep->smoke->author->Codex-gate->fail-loud behavioral replay asserting the 3 proofs FIRE on a real corpus->commit). RC-D (consolidation, multi-source baskets) is proof #2's feeder = build alongside. Faithfulness NEVER relaxed (verified-compose = abstractive prose w/ provenance tokens -> deterministic strict_verify -> verbatim K-span fallback; LLM ORGANIZES, cannot FABRICATE). The inline corroborator surface is ALREADY wired+firing (test-proven) so multi-member baskets WILL surface once consolidation produces them + STORM-outline widens the cited-claim set.",
