    }
  },
  "resume_protocol_API_error_or_restart": "On ANY wake / API-error / restart: (1) read the ssot files above FIRST; (2) find active_track + active_step here; (3) CONTINUE from active_step â€” NEVER redo a completed step (check git log + the verdict files for what already landed); (4) if a Workflow/Codex/VM run was in flight, CHECK it (TaskList + the output/verdict file + transcript mtime) before acting; (5) update active_step here after every step so the next resume is exact.",
  "monitoring_calibration_LESSON": "A long Workflow can run 45+ MINUTES. A 0-byte output file + a transient process-count=0 is NOT death â€” the structured result is written only at completion, and process counts cycle. NEVER declare a workflow dead / restart it without BOTH: (a) the harness task-notification has NOT arrived AND the task is absent from TaskList, AND (b) the agent transcript .jsonl mtime is idle > 5 min. False-restarting a healthy workflow wastes tokens and can corrupt the working tree (git-stash gymnastics).",
  "discipline_rules": [
    "Every build = GitHub issue -> grep adjacent -> offline smoke -> Claude authors diff -> Codex diff-gate -> fail-loud behavioral replay in the SAME change -> commit on APPROVE.",
    "Surgical code edits = author directly (main agent) + Codex-gate; reserve the Workflow FUNCTION for research/review/audit FAN-OUT (it drifts on surgical file edits â€” git-stash gymnastics observed in the FIX-P0-B build agent).",
    "NO drift: one active_track at a time (or independent parallel tracks, each disciplined); no scope expansion; the SSOT is the master plan sequence.",
    "Faithfulness NEVER relaxed; always-release preserved; generalize (no clinical hardcode); no grandfathered tools; for unknowns research 2026 + adopt proven parts.",
    "Never self-pause; stop only on #1-on-both / real halt / operator stop.",
    "CONTINUOUS EXECUTION — do NOT yield-to-wait. After launching a background Codex gate / run, IMMEDIATELY build the next independent piece in the SAME turn; check background tasks opportunistically when you finish other work (foreground a gate only if there is no other work). Each turn does MANY steps (build A -> bg-gate A -> build B -> check gate A -> commit A -> bg-gate B -> build C ...). ScheduleWakeup ONLY when genuinely blocked: a multi-hour VM run with no parallel work, OR a real stop condition. An idle ~10-min ScheduleWakeup gap between cheap build steps is the BUG (operator-flagged 2026-06-20).",
    "LAUNCH Codex gates / trackable long tasks via the Bash tool run_in_background:true (NOT nohup &) — the harness re-invokes you the MOMENT the task exits (event-driven), so you commit immediately with NO idle ScheduleWakeup gap. nohup detaches from the harness -> no notification -> forces polling -> the idle gap the operator flagged. ScheduleWakeup is ONLY a long fallback heartbeat for things the harness cannot track (a VM run)."
  ],
  "updated_note": "see CAMPAIGN.md tail for timestamp",
  "keystone_finding_2026_06_20": {
    "finding": "run7 is a RESUME run: resume.log shows it reloaded a post_generation(raw_drafts=6) checkpoint and REPLAYED 6 legacy-shaped sections; generation never re-ran. So run7 CANNOT diagnose the breadth bug.",
    "storm_flag": "PG_STORM_OUTLINE_SECTIONS IS ON in gate-B slate (run_gate_b.py:910=\"1\"); wiring is correct (run_honest_sweep_r3.py:5323 captures storm_outline -> :8685 threads it to the generator).",
    "implication": "No evidence STORM-outline is broken. The decisive breadth verdict requires a FRESH run (P6). Do NOT over-build breadth fixes against a resume artifact.",
    "sequencing": "Fix1 synthesis (analysis lever 18%) + real abstractive writer (replaces broken short-writer stub) in parallel -> land fetch-shell -> P5 preflight -> P6 fresh GLM-5.2 run measures breadth decisively.",
    "advisor_blessing": "Design (PHASE4_DESIGN_BASIS_2026.md Fix1) blessed: per-basket pool default, harness-first, relational-quantifier->both-sides/labeled guard. Build Fix1 SECOND after keystone-first check (done)."
  },
  "fetchshell_fix_status": "DONE — I-beatboth-001 #1276 committed 4681fda5, Codex diff gate iter-3 APPROVE (0 P0/P1). DeepTRACE polish (won board). Final cert = P6 fresh run.",
  "prc_faithfulness_hole_2026_06_20": {
    "finding": "PR-c (verified_compose composition rebuild, the I-arch-011 breadth-fix core) is UNCOMMITTED but its flag PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE is committed-on in the Gate-B slate (run_gate_b.py:912). Codex prc_core re-gate today 03:34 = REQUEST_CHANGES, 2 P1 faithfulness holes, working tree unfixed.",
    "hole_1": "_basket_member_regions (:120) + _basket_scoped_pool (:86) accept ALL supporting_members, not SUPPORTS-only (contrast _basket_supports_members :76) -> unsupported in-basket member can render as verified.",
    "hole_2": "_assemble_baskets sets direct_quote = full row span -> _member_global_span recovers (0,len(row)) -> same-source cross-claim drift passes.",
    "inheritance": "I-beatboth-002 F1-1 (#1278) is built on this base and INHERITS both holes; its harness masked them with SUPPORTS-only short-span members. F1-1 is dual-gated+audited but HELD (uncommitted) pending the fix.",
    "fix": "URGENT issue #1279, workflow wf_5125d51a-c48: surgical tightening (SUPPORTS-only regions/pool; claim-local spans), harness-first reproduce-then-close, Codex re-gate. Faithfulness engine UNTOUCHED.",
    "commit_order": "PR-c (with #1279 fix) FIRST -> then F1-1 (#1278) re-verified on the fixed base. MUST be committed before P6 (else flag-on-code-missing silent no-op).",
    "status": "RESOLVED + COMMITTED 9df1c5ee. #1279 closed. Both P1s tightened (SUPPORTS-only regions/pool; claim-local span). PR-c + F1-1 now committed; breadth fix no longer flag-on-code-missing for P6."
  },
  "KEYSTONE_VERIFIED_2026_06_20": "section-1.4 fired-in-output + CODE-LEVEL verification of why STORM-outline (the breadth keystone) never widened the sections. Supersedes the older active_step (which thought #1268 composition was UNMERGED -- it IS merged + flags-on). FACT 1 (probe log outputs/prc_render_probe/render_probe.log): ZERO 'STORM-outline section scaffold' log lines; the built outline was LEGACY V30-P2 = '3 contract + 6 enrichment sections' (line 843-844: Foundational_Theory/Empirical_Displacement/Generative_AI_Evidence/Background/Key Findings/Evidence and Analysis/Comparative Assessment/Implications/Limitations, ok=True fallback=False). verified-compose DID fire on all 6 enrichment sections (generation re-ran) -> NOT a generation-skip; specifically the STORM OUTLINE could not fire. FACT 2 (code run_honest_sweep_r3.py:5326): _storm_outline (threaded to the generator) is populated ONLY IF (not _resume_active) AND (not _resume_from_fetch) AND PG_STORM_ENABLED_IN_BENCHMARK in (1,true,True). The probe was --resume (reloaded POST-SELECTION corpus_snapshot sources=836/evidence_rows=742) -> _resume_active=True -> STORM block SKIPPED -> _storm_outline=[] -> _build_storm_outline_section_plans([]) returns None (multi_section_generator.py:1876 'if not storm_outline: return None') -> legacy. STORM-outline STRUCTURALLY CANNOT fire on a resume. EVERY diagnostic artifact (run7 post-gen resume + prc_render_probe post-selection resume) is a resume -> ALL fell to legacy -> THAT is why breadth looked collapsed in every artifact (NOT a STORM bug, NOT too-few-sections). FACT 3 (two-flag check, the landmine I checked for): PRODUCER PG_STORM_ENABLED_IN_BENCHMARK (run_honest_sweep_r3.py:5326, STORM-interview phase produces storm_outline) is DISTINCT from CONSUMER PG_STORM_OUTLINE_SECTIONS (multi_section_generator.py:6779). BOTH are in the gate-B slate force-on + preflight-required: producer run_gate_b.py:471='1' (+:1016 force/:1106 preflight), consumer run_gate_b.py:910='1'. test_benchmark_stack_activation_meta007.py:99 asserts producer=='1'. So a FRESH run_gate_b run (no --resume): _resume_active=False + both flags ON -> STORM block FIRES -> storm_outline produced -> scaffold consumed -> wider sections. CONCLUSION: breadth machinery is BUILT + WIRED + flags-on; NEVER measured because every artifact is a resume that bypasses the producer. Building MORE breadth machinery (RC-D, more sections) against resume artifacts = the operator-warned trap ('do NOT over-build breadth fixes against a resume artifact'). DECISIVE next action = P5 preflight (confirm STORM fires + the 8 committed fixes activate on a fresh-run canary per the I-arch-005 'committed != wired' lesson) -> P6 FRESH run (the only DRB-II breadth measurement). Whether STORM WIDENS *enough* is itself a fresh-run measurement (the interview is an LLM phase). Local render probe pid 35232 is DEAD (D8 sentinel POST total-deadline timeouts 07:56-07:58, no manifest.json, report.md is a 07:35 pre-D8 draft). Advisor-consulted the fresh-run-vs-build-more fork before authoring.",
  "D8_COMPLETION_BLOCKER_2026_06_20": "ADVISOR-reframed tightest constraint = can a render COMPLETE through D8, NOT 'does STORM widen'. TRACED to a FACT: the dead probe four_role_compute_progress.json = {done:24, total:1519} -- D8 settled only 24 of 1519 claims in ~23min (07:35-07:58, ~57s/claim) before death. CAUSE (probe log 1199-1277): the SENTINEL role POST repeatedly exceeds PG_ROLE_TRANSPORT_TOTAL_S=300 (run_gate_b.py:872) and force-closes+retries(3x), 12+ times 07:40-07:58 -> each claim's sentinel verdict up to 300s x3=900s. NOT a worker-count bug: D8 IS 6-parallel (sweep_integration.py:155 _CLAIM_WORKERS=max(1,PG_FOUR_ROLE_CLAIM_WORKERS default 6), read AT IMPORT; :600 ThreadPoolExecutor; FIX-C's PG_PARALLEL_VERIFY controls the SEPARATE provenance findings-verify loop, NOT D8). The forensic's 'D8 serial' was really 6-parallel-but-each-claim-provider-bound. ROOT BLOCKER = sentinel(minimax-m2)+mirror(glm) OpenRouter providers TRICKLING/timing-out (the I-arch-007 hang class; minimax sentinel timed out on BOTH boxes same window). Healthy ~10s/claim/6-workers -> 1519 completes ~42min (forensic '45min if parallel'); at 300s-timeout ~24hr -> render dies. COMPLETION is gated PURELY by sentinel/mirror provider health, not code. 1519-claim scale is NOT the blocker if providers are healthy. DISCRIMINATING CHECK = a live provider health-probe NOW (does minimax-m2/glm respond <30s or hang toward 300s?): transient(healthy)=launch the fresh P6 (STORM fires + completes ~2.5hr); systemic(trickle)=fix provider routing OR the glm-5.2 upgrade before spending a 2.5hr run that dies again.",
  "MODEL_LOCK_INCONSISTENCY_2026_06_20": "BEFORE launching the operator-signed glm-5.1->5.2 mirror upgrade run, found a 3-WAY model-config inconsistency that would kill a fresh run at verify_lock preflight (caught pre-spend). (1) LOCK FILE config/architecture/polaris_runtime_lock.yaml @HEAD 71535441 = the DORMANT 'GLM-5.2 COMPARISON ARM' (committed f877a815, comment 'EXPERIMENT ONLY do NOT merge to production lock'): generator=z-ai/glm-5.2, mirror=deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro, family_policy all_distinct. (2) CANONICAL PIN docs/canonical_pin.txt pins SHA 1dd2e788 but the file's actual SHA=90feabd7 -> PIN DRIFT (documented HALT condition; pre-existing, not mine -- pin never updated when the comparison arm landed). (3) EFFECTIVE RUN STACK (what the code actually resolves, NOT the lock) = production: generator=deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro + mirror/side-judges=z-ai/glm-5.1 (entailment_judge.py:82 _DEFAULT_ENTAILMENT_MODEL, credibility_judge_caller.py:28 _DEFAULT_MODEL, semantic_conflict_detector.py:69 all default glm-5.1; openrouter_provider_routing.yaml mirror=glm-5.1) + sentinel=minimax/minimax-m2 + judge=qwen/qwen3.6. The render probe CONFIRMS effective: it used deepseek gen + glm-5.1 credibility. So the lock file is dormant verification text that does NOT drive the run, AND it disagrees with both the pin and reality. CONSEQUENCE: a FRESH run's verify_lock.py preflight asserts code-defaults==lock; lock-gen=glm-5.2 vs effective-gen=deepseek MISMATCH -> the fresh run dies at preflight. So the lock<->code<->pin MUST be reconciled to ONE consistent stack before P6. Operator chose 'sign off glm-5.2' (the mirror upgrade). DECISION NEEDED (operator): (A) production generator deepseek-v4-pro + mirror/entailment/credibility/semantic-conflict upgraded glm-5.1->glm-5.2 [= the minimal signed mirror change, keeps the proven 1M-ctx generator, 4 roles stay distinct families], OR (B) full all-GLM-5.2 per the campaign banner [generator->glm-5.2 too; needs family_policy relaxation since gen+mirror both glm = self-judge; bigger change]. RECOMMEND (A). Then reconcile: rewrite the lock to the chosen stack + update canonical_pin.txt SHA + set PG_MIRROR_MODEL/PG_ENTAILMENT_MODEL/PG_CREDIBILITY_JUDGE_MODEL=z-ai/glm-5.2 in the gate-B slate (LAW VI) + flip the 3 code defaults glm-5.1->glm-5.2 so verify_lock passes + verify glm-5.2 real max_completion_tokens via /api/v1/models (sec 9.1.8). Health-probe latency glm-5.2=2.7s (Z.AI) vs glm-5.1=11.7s (Chutes) = ~4x faster mirror, also speeds the ~49min credibility-pass bottleneck. NOT yet edited -- await operator stack choice (signed lock + pin = operator-governance, sec 9.1.8 'model must be RIGHT, always double-check').",
  "NEXT_ACTION_2026_06_20_pm": "OPERATOR DECISIONS: (1) stack = (A) deepseek-v4-pro generator + mirror/side-judges glm-5.1->glm-5.2 (keep proven gen; 4 roles distinct families); (2) maximize pipeline PARALLELISM (speed) + maximize resume CHECKPOINTS incl persist storm_outline so a --resume can fire STORM. Issue I-beatboth-008 = #1285. glm-5.2 verified: ctx 1048576 / max_completion 131072 (bigger than 5.1's 202752/65535, ~4x faster: 2.7s Z.AI vs 11.7s Chutes). IN FLIGHT: read-only map Workflow w8rfto7v0 (wf_4ecabfca-00c) fan-out 4 Explore agents -> (A) every glm-5.1->5.2 mirror locus + verify_lock preflight asserts + glm-5.2 providers + lock-rewrite-to-deepseek-gen+glm5.2-mirror, (B) every parallelism knob (D8 PG_FOUR_ROLE_CLAIM_WORKERS=6, PG_PARALLEL_VERIFY=16, PG_CREDIBILITY_PASS_MAX_INFLIGHT, PG_MAX_PARALLEL_SECTIONS=3, distill/fetch) + safe maxima, (C) checkpoint/resume mechanism + the storm_outline-persist fix locus + resume-granularity additions, (D) fresh-run preflight landmine sweep. ON MAP RETURN: author surgically (discipline_rules: surgical edits author-direct + Codex-gate, NOT via Workflow) -> lock rewrite + canonical_pin SHA update + 3 code-default flips + slate env (PG_MIRROR/ENTAILMENT/CREDIBILITY_JUDGE_MODEL=z-ai/glm-5.2) + parallelism slate bumps + storm_outline persist/restore + new checkpoints -> offline smoke (verify_lock PASS, imports, family_policy) -> Codex diff-gate (lock mutation policy requires Codex APPROVE) run_in_background -> fail-loud behavioral replay -> commit on APPROVE -> P5 preflight (STORM fires N>9 + 8 fixes activate on a fresh canary) -> P6 FRESH run (first real DRB-II breadth measurement). Faithfulness engine byte-identical throughout; checkpoints DATA-ONLY (resume re-runs all gates). F1-1 #1284 DEFERRED (advisor: inert without RC-D; decide RC-D-vs-F1-1 AFTER the fresh run gives real collapsed/breadth data).",
  "ALLGLM52_DECISION_AND_SPEC_2026_06_20": "OPERATOR (informed, repeated 3x; all-GLM-5.2 was pre-decided last session, I drifted by re-litigating two-family -> feedback memory written): FULL all-GLM-5.2 for gen+mirror (sentinel=minimax-m2 + judge=qwen KEPT = 2 independent D8 adjudicators). MAX reasoning (xhigh) + MAX ctx (1M) + max_tokens + STABLEST server. Two-family relaxation operator-approved + must be DOCUMENTED (not silent); deterministic faithfulness floor (strict_verify/provenance/span/numeric/D8-logic) stays byte-identical. PROVIDER PROBE (glm-5.2, 3x, max_tokens=2000): Friendli 3/3 contentful 3.3s 1M-ctx/1048576-out = STABLEST+FASTEST+MAXCAP (LEAD); Novita 3/3 6.7s 131072; Z.AI 3/3 9.8s first-party 131072; Phala 3/3 22.3s 1048576 (slow); Fireworks+Cloudflare 2/3 (429) DROP. CHAIN = [friendli, novita, z-ai, phala] for BOTH generator + mirror. FAMILY-GATE RELAX (crown-jewel, hand-author): check_family_segregation (openrouter_client.py:711 raises on same-family; called by 6 side-judges entailment_judge:440 / credibility_judge_caller:196 / semantic_conflict_detector:626 / relevance_judge:197 / live_judge:140 / external_evaluator:847) -> add env PG_PERMIT_GENERATOR_EVALUATOR_SAME_FAMILY (default '0'=safeguard ON; '1'=LOG LOUD disclosure + return instead of raise). validate_role_families (openrouter_client.py:725): allowed_collisions DOES apply under all_distinct (code 768-773; docstring 'ignored' is WRONG) -> lock allowed_collisions [[generator,mirror]]. crown-jewel test tests/crown_jewels/test_cj_001 must stay GREEN (default-OFF preserves the raise). glm-5.2 REASONING LANDMINE: _ALWAYS_REASON_MODELS (openrouter_client.py:798) + _REASONING_FIRST_MODELS (:808) include glm-5.1 + deepseek but NOT glm-5.2; probe showed glm-5.2 contentful 3/3 @2000tok (returns content, not reasoning-first-empty) BUT under xhigh + huge generator prompts add glm-5.2 to BOTH sets (same lineage as 5.1 = same reasoning-first shape; the 40%-reasoning-cap prevents xhigh starving content -> avoids the glm-5.1 xhigh-blank class). EDIT SPEC (current tree = A-edits DONE: 5 code defaults->glm-5.2, routing mirror->glm-5.2, lock mirror=glm-5.2/gen=deepseek, pin=85be5f27): REMAINING -> (1) lock generator deepseek->z-ai/glm-5.2 family glm + family_policy allowed_collisions [['generator','mirror']]; (2) routing generator block model->z-ai/glm-5.2 order [friendli,novita,z-ai,phala] + reorder mirror to friendli-lead [friendli,novita,z-ai,phala]; (3) openrouter_client.py:577 PG_GENERATOR_MODEL default deepseek->z-ai/glm-5.2; (4) check_family_segregation permit flag; (5) add glm-5.2 to _ALWAYS_REASON_MODELS + _REASONING_FIRST_MODELS; (6) slate run_gate_b.py: PG_GENERATOR_MODEL+PG_MIRROR_MODEL+PG_ENTAILMENT_MODEL+PG_EVALUATOR_MODEL+PG_CREDIBILITY_JUDGE_MODEL=z-ai/glm-5.2 + PG_PERMIT_GENERATOR_EVALUATOR_SAME_FAMILY=1 + PG_FOUR_ROLE_REASONING_EFFORT medium->xhigh (line 1402) + 11 parallelism knobs (FOUR_ROLE_CLAIM_WORKERS=12/PARALLEL_VERIFY 16->24/CREDIBILITY_PASS_MAX_INFLIGHT 16->20/MAX_PARALLEL_SECTIONS=6/DISTILL_MAX_PARALLEL 8->12/DISTILL_MICROBATCH_SIZE=2/LIVE_RETRIEVER_MAX_WORKERS 16->24/LIVE_RETRIEVER_PER_HOST_CONCURRENT=6/BYPASS_MAX_INFLIGHT=20/STORM_CONCURRENCY=8/MAX_CONCURRENT_LLM 5->8); (7) recompute canonical_pin.txt lock SHA after the lock rewrite; (8) storm_outline persist/restore (run_honest_sweep_r3.py persist@5407 + restore@~4685) per ckpt map. THEN verify_lock (code_defaults_match + family permit) -> Codex diff-gate via Claude Codex Workflow -> commit. Issue #1285. EXECUTE-VIA: Claude Codex Workflow for SMOKE+GATE (operator 3x); crown-jewel family-gate edit hand-authored for safety.",
  "ALLGLM52_BUILD_DONE_GATE_BLOCKER_2026_06_21": "Claude Codex Workflow wpw6es5zg DONE: all 8 all-GLM-5.2 edits applied (lock gen->glm-5.2 family glm + allowed_collisions[[generator,mirror]]; routing friendli-lead [friendli,novita,z-ai,phala] gen+mirror; openrouter_client PG_GENERATOR_MODEL default->glm-5.2 + PG_PERMIT_GENERATOR_EVALUATOR_SAME_FAMILY default-OFF disclosure block before the same-family raise + glm-5.2 in _ALWAYS_REASON_MODELS; .env got 7 keys PG_*_MODEL=glm-5.2 + permit=1 + reasoning xhigh; canonical_pin lock SHA=57f34a4a726a1be46fc8e713ba0226dee05054a879b97145138e90702aeb4225). Codex diff-gate = APPROVE 0 P0. BUT build agent caught (verified by me) a real BLOCKER my spec missed: the lock allowed_collisions is NOT honored by 3 run-path family gates -> verify_lock exits 1. (a) scripts/architecture/verify_lock.py:104-113 = hardcoded all_distinct loop, 'allowed_collisions is empty' literal, never reads family_policy.allowed_collisions = CONFIRMED BLOCKS (verify_lock canonical-pinned line13 60c7fb58 -> edit needs pin update). (b) scripts/dr_benchmark/run_gate_b.py:234-262 assert_four_role_families_distinct = MODE-AWARE: openrouter mode compares gen LOCK-family ('glm' now) vs verifier BENCHMARK-families (benchmark_verifier_family: mirror 'z-ai', sentinel 'ibm-granite', judge 'qwen') -> may PASS by label-mismatch (glm != z-ai) even though gen+mirror both glm -> VERIFY what benchmark_verifier_family('mirror') returns; fix to honor allowed_collisions either way. (c) src/polaris_graph/benchmark/pathB_runner.py:104 validate_role_families(slug_by_role) no allowed_collisions arg -> []->raises (validate_role_families ITSELF honors allowed_collisions at openrouter_client.py:768-773 when PASSED; path-B = sovereign-serving, may not be on benchmark run path). FIX (the natural completion of the operator-approved relaxation, NOT a new decision): make all 3 gates read lock family_policy.allowed_collisions (SSOT). + test_cj_001 hermetic: add monkeypatch.delenv('PG_PERMIT_GENERATOR_EVALUATOR_SAME_FAMILY',raising=False) (the .env permit=1 autoloaded by src/__init__.py contaminates the bare pytest -> RED; CI has no .env so CI green; proven .env-artifact not code defect). Model diff (4 files) = .codex/I-beatboth-008/codex_diff_allglm52.patch (APPROVE). NEXT: gate-fix Claude Codex Workflow (investigate+fix the 3 gates + test + verify_lock pin) -> SMOKE verify_lock PASS + gates permit gen+mirror-glm but raise a non-allowed collision + crown-jewel green -> re-gate combined diff -> COMMIT (lock+routing+openrouter_client+canonical_pin+verify_lock+run_gate_b+pathB_runner+test_cj_001; .env gitignored). THEN commit-2 parallelism+storm-checkpoint. THEN P5 preflight -> P6 fresh run.",
  "COMMIT2_STORM_CHECKPOINT_SPEC_VERIFIED_2026_06_21": "Verified the storm_outline persist/restore loci against run_honest_sweep_r3.py (read-only, while gate-fix wf w1u45js9y runs). PRODUCE: line 5406 `_storm_outline = list(_storm_out.get('storm_outline', []) or [])` inside the STORM block (fresh-only; 5407 sets telemetry outline_sections). PERSIST: write storm_outline.json (atomic, [s.model_dump() for s in _storm_outline]) right after 5407, guarded `if (not _resume_active) and (not _resume_from_fetch)`. RESTORE point = the resume-load block lines 4676-4684 (corpus_snapshot@4676 / fetch_snapshot@4678 / A12 checkpoints@4683-4684). SUBTLETY (map agent C MISSED this -> a naive restore is a SILENT NO-OP): execution order is 4684(restore) THEN 5325(`_storm_outline = []` init) THEN 5326(STORM block, SKIPPED on resume). So restoring into `_storm_outline` at 4684 gets CLOBBERED by the 5325 init. CORRECT WIRING: at ~4684 load storm_outline.json into a SEPARATE var `_resumed_storm_outline` (fail-loud on corrupt, None if absent, both resume paths); then CHANGE line 5325 from `_storm_outline = []` to `_storm_outline = list(_resumed_storm_outline or [])` -> fresh: None->[]->STORM populates; resume: restored outline survives (5326 skipped) -> threads to the generator @8768 (already wired). Behavioral replay must assert: a --resume run with a banked storm_outline.json FIRES the STORM scaffold (log '[multi_section] STORM-outline section scaffold: N sections', N>9) = the §-1.4 fired-in-output proof. This makes resumes valid breadth runs (operator's 'more checkpoints for resume' + fixes the KEYSTONE_VERIFIED resume-cant-fire-STORM gap). Commit-2 = this + the 11 parallelism slate knobs (mind PG_FOUR_ROLE_CLAIM_WORKERS import-timing sweep_integration.py:155) via Claude Codex Workflow after the gate-fix commits (both touch run_gate_b/run_honest_sweep -> serialize after gate-fix).",
  "ALLGLM52_ITER1_REQUEST_CHANGES_ITER2_INFLIGHT_2026_06_21": "Combined Codex gate (gate-fix wf w1u45js9y) iter 1/5 = REQUEST_CHANGES, 0 P0, 3 P1, 2 P2 (convergence continue). Codex confirmed faithfulness engine UNTOUCHED + verify_lock/pathB_runner allowed_collisions wiring correct, but caught 3 REAL all-GLM-5.2 COMPLETENESS gaps my §-1.1 audit + the build missed: P1-1 run_gate_b passes gen+mirror by LABEL MISMATCH (generator family from lock='glm' vs benchmark_verifier_family provider-prefix='z-ai' via openrouter_role_transport._family_from_slug=slug.split('/')[0]) -> allowed_collisions NOT the SSOT in that gate (emptying it would still pass). P1-2 openrouter_role_transport.py:160 _BENCHMARK_LINEUP_DEFAULT_SLUG[mirror] still z-ai/glm-5.1 (slate doesn't force PG_MIRROR_MODEL) -> a run could be silently not-all-GLM-5.2. P1-3 openrouter_client.py:62 OPENROUTER_MODEL default still deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro -> no-model caller violates the lock. P2: lock generator released 2026-04-24 (stale deepseek date, should be 2026-06) + mirror comment still says deepseek-gen; test_pathB_runner:19-21 constants stale. ITER-2 wf wb3qvrtp1 IN FLIGHT: P1-1=derive generator family by provider-prefix of its active slug (PG_GENERATOR_MODEL or lock model_slug, reuse _family_from_slug) so gen+mirror BOTH 'z-ai' collide -> allowed_collisions genuinely enforces (SMOKE PROOF: emptying allowed_collisions -> RAISES); P1-2=transport mirror default ->glm-5.2 + stale comment; P1-3=OPENROUTER_DEFAULT_MODEL default ->glm-5.2; P2=lock released/comment + re-pin + test constants. SMOKE proves genuine enforcement + mirror/client defaults=5.2 + crown-jewel green; Codex re-gate iter 2/5. verify_lock_ok=false in iter-1 smoke = BENIGN (tests_pass checkpoint hardwired False in report() so it never exits 0; --consistency exits 0; code_defaults_match OK -- NOT a regression). ON iter-2 APPROVE -> commit the committed files (lock+routing+openrouter_client+openrouter_role_transport+canonical_pin+verify_lock+run_gate_b+pathB_runner+test_cj_001+test_pathB_runner; .env gitignored) ref #1285 -> commit-2 (parallelism + storm checkpoint per COMMIT2_STORM_CHECKPOINT_SPEC_VERIFIED) -> P5 -> P6. PRE-EXISTING (follow-up issue, NOT this scope): 7 stale test_pathB_runner failures + out_root str/Path TypeError run_gate_b.py:2120 (hits test_benchmark_stack_activation_meta007 too).",
  "ALLGLM52_ITER2_APPROVE_ITER3_INFLIGHT_2026_06_21": "Combined Codex gate iter-2/5 = APPROVE (0 P0, 0 P1, 2 P2 non-blocking, accept_remaining). The 3 P1s + 2 P2s CLOSED; P1-1 enforcement PROVEN (run_gate_b derives generator family via _family_from_slug on the active slug -> gen=z-ai==mirror=z-ai real collision honored ONLY via lock allowed_collisions; emptying it RAISES). Faithfulness engine byte-identical. New lock SHA d7fe7275 (pin updated). 2 CI-green items remained -> iter-3 wf wafc8lh19 IN FLIGHT: (A) .env stale line OPENROUTER_DEFAULT_MODEL=deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro (load_dotenv shadows the glm-5.2 code default -> no-model client = deepseek, NOT all-GLM-5.2) -> .env value ->z-ai/glm-5.2 (smoke client_default_is_52 was FALSE because of this); (B) stale-test-fixture cascade: P1-2 (mirror default 5.1->5.2) broke a previously-GREEN test + 12 others in tests/roles/test_openrouter_role_transport_meta007.py + tests/dr_benchmark/test_benchmark_stack_activation_meta007.py + tests/dr_benchmark/test_super_heavy_preflight_icred013.py (hardcoded z-ai/glm-5.1 / deepseek-gen / 4-distinct-families) -> align to all-GLM-5.2 (gen+mirror allowed-collision; each re-premised distinctness test KEEPS a negative case that RAISES on an unlisted collision -- two-family NOT weakened). PRE-EXISTING (filed I-beatboth-009 #1286, NOT this scope): gemma env-leak test_pathB_runner._full_power_env (5 gate-lifecycle fails) + out_root str/Path TypeError run_gate_b.py:2134. ON iter-3 APPROVE -> commit the 13 committed files (.env gitignored) ref #1285 + post to #1285 -> commit-2 (parallelism + storm checkpoint) -> P5 -> P6. Codex gate iter count: 3/5.",
  "ALLGLM52_COMMITTED_COMMIT2_NEXT_2026_06_21": "I-beatboth-008 (#1285) all-GLM-5.2 model reconcile COMMITTED a04cbf23 (13 files, 406+/278-; Codex APPROVE iter-3/5; verify_lock --consistency exit0; lock pin d7fe7275 + verify_lock pin MATCH no-drift; only the 13 intended files, pathB_run_gate.py [pre-existing I-safety-002b dirty] correctly EXCLUDED). Final stack: gen+mirror=z-ai/glm-5.2, sentinel=minimax-m2, judge=qwen; Friendli-led routing; two-family relaxed via default-OFF PG_PERMIT_GENERATOR_EVALUATOR_SAME_FAMILY + lock allowed_collisions[[generator,mirror]] as SSOT enforced by verify_lock+run_gate_b+pathB_runner (unlisted collision RAISES; crown-jewel green); faithfulness engine byte-identical; models in .env; xhigh; 1M ctx. #1286 tracks pre-existing gemma+out_root test debt. NEXT = commit-2 via Claude Codex Workflow: (A) 11 parallelism slate knobs in run_gate_b.py [PG_FOUR_ROLE_CLAIM_WORKERS=12 (MUST rebind sweep_integration._CLAIM_WORKERS=12 after slate OR set before import -- it is import-read @sweep_integration.py:155; smoke MUST prove _CLAIM_WORKERS==12 takes effect)/PARALLEL_VERIFY 16->24/CREDIBILITY_PASS_MAX_INFLIGHT 16->20/MAX_PARALLEL_SECTIONS=6/DISTILL_MAX_PARALLEL 8->12/DISTILL_MICROBATCH_SIZE=2/LIVE_RETRIEVER_MAX_WORKERS 16->24/PER_HOST_CONCURRENT=6/BYPASS_MAX_INFLIGHT=20/STORM_CONCURRENCY=8/MAX_CONCURRENT_LLM 5->8] + (B) storm_outline persist@run_honest_sweep_r3.py:5407 (atomic storm_outline.json, [s.model_dump() for s in _storm_outline], guard not-resume) + restore@~4684 into _resumed_storm_outline (StormOutlineSection(**d)) + CHANGE line 5325 `_storm_outline = []` -> `_storm_outline = list(_resumed_storm_outline or [])` (the clobber-fix -- restore at 4684 else clobbered by the 5325 init) + behavioral test (restore-not-clobbered: banked storm_outline.json -> _storm_outline populated after the 5325 seed) -> Codex gate -> commit. THEN P5 preflight -> P6 fresh run. faithfulness untouched; only worker COUNTS + a DATA-ONLY checkpoint (resume re-runs all gates).",
  "OVERNIGHT_HAMSTER_PLAN_2026_06_21": "Operator went to sleep ~02:30 local 2026-06-21; AUTHORIZED a full AUTONOMOUS OVERNIGHT HAMSTER LOOP. MILITARY ORDER (each phase COMPLETE+VERIFIED before the next, no skipping). Claude Codex Workflow = engine; Codex = only gate; faithfulness NEVER relaxed (only the operator-approved two-family is relaxed, logged); keep GitHub (#1270/#1285/#1286 + campaign) + docs (loop_state, MASTER_PLAN.md) updated at phase boundaries; announce each Workflow + each PAID launch (operator blind, reads by ear); plain point-form, full-list-every-run, no cheerleading. SEQUENCE: (1) commit-2 wf wnm4330ik gate APPROVE -> commit the 3 files ref #1285 (REQUEST_CHANGES<5 -> fix+re-gate; ==5 -> force-APPROVE §8.3.1). (2) P5 PREFLIGHT (Claude Codex Workflow): a FRESH-run canary proving the KEYSTONE -- STORM-outline scaffold FIRES with N>9 sections on a FRESH (non-resume) run (grep '[multi_section] STORM-outline section scaffold: N sections') + the 8 committed fixes + all-GLM-5.2 + the 11 parallelism knobs ACTIVATE on the run path + D8 dispatches at the ~12-worker cadence (NOT 1/3-5s) + verify_lock/family gates pass at preflight; kill after the early signals confirm (NO full spend). If STORM<N>9 OR D8 serial OR a fix dead-on-arrival -> THAT is the next bug, fix it FIRST (the I-arch-005 committed!=wired lesson). (3) P6 FRESH run (no --resume) on the VM fast-glm or local healthy-providers = the DECISIVE DRB-II + DeepTRACE measurement; FORENSIC-MONITOR real-time LINE-BY-LINE every tick (feedback_monitor_means_line_by_line_forensic: fan a forensic Workflow reading full log+reasoning_trace+raw LLM IO+citations, judge reasoning soundness + the faithfulness gates; REPORT the DECOMPOSED cited-source breadth estimate each tick per feedback_monitoring_must_estimate_cited_source_count; watch four_role_compute_progress done/total + STORM fire + glm/minimax cadence + cost). (4) ON P6 COMPLETE: §-1.1 line-by-line audit of report.md (claim-by-claim vs fetched spans; breadth = distinct cited [N] in pack_drb2.answer_body decomposed by section; synthesis-vs-enumeration; fabrication/over-drop/mis-cite). (5) BENCHMARK BOTH SCOREBOARDS: DeepTRACE (pack_deeptrace -> third_party/answer-engine-eval/Venkit.et.al.2024/populate_scores.py greedy_set_cover S1..S10) + DeepResearch-Bench-II (third_party/DeepResearch-Bench-II/run_evaluation.py). (6) SUMMARIZE ALL PROBLEMS = the honest gaps to #1-on-both (full list, every run, plain point-form). (7) RESEARCH FIXES (2026 frontier, primary-source-verified, no grandfather). (8) HAMSTER LOOP: build each fix via Claude Codex Workflow (issue->grep->smoke->author->Codex-gate->fail-loud replay->commit) -> re-run -> re-score -> repeat until #1-on-BOTH leaderboards. STOP ONLY on #1-on-both / real halt / operator stop. Providers healthy (Friendli glm-5.2 3.3s / minimax 1.8s / deepseek 0.4s). Spend authorized. GOAL=POLARIS #1 on BOTH DeepTRACE + DeepResearch-Bench-II (project_goal_number_one_deeptrace_drbench2).",
  "COMMIT1_OMISSION_FIXED_COMMIT2_V2_2026_06_21": "TWO catches handled this tick (autonomous overnight). (1) commit-2 build-1 (wf wnm4330ik) DIED on API stream-idle timeout (recurring long-build failure) -> smoke/gate honestly reported 'commit-2 does not exist' + refused to fabricate (LAW II). Re-launched as commit-2 V2 wf w9m7k2j1w with a SPLIT build (2 parallel smaller agents: A=run_gate_b.py parallelism, B=run_honest_sweep_r3.py storm) to beat the timeout. (2) THE SMOKE CAUGHT A REAL OMISSION: a04cbf23 (#1285 model reconcile) DROPPED the 3 evaluator-family side-judge defaults (entailment_judge.py:82 / credibility_judge_caller.py:28 / semantic_conflict_detector.py:69) when the combined-diff file list churned iter-1->iter-3 -- they were uncommitted with the correct glm-5.1->glm-5.2 edits. COMMITTED the completeness fix 90e68f32 (3 files; they map to mirror via legacy_compat so default must be glm-5.2; run already used glm-5.2 via .env but the committed default now matches; verify_lock --consistency still exit0). #1285 all-GLM-5.2 model reconcile now COMPLETE: a04cbf23 + 90e68f32. HEAD=90e68f32. NEXT: commit-2 V2 w9m7k2j1w gate -> on APPROVE commit (run_gate_b.py + run_honest_sweep_r3.py + scripts/iarch_beatboth008_commit2_replay_harness.py) ref #1285 -> P5 preflight -> P6 (OVERNIGHT_HAMSTER_PLAN_2026_06_21 is the binding sequence). LESSON: split big Codex-Workflow builds into smaller agents (the stream-idle-timeout bites long single-agent builds); ALWAYS verify the commit included EXACTLY the intended files (git show <sha> --name-only vs the diff's file list) -- a churning file list can silently drop files.",
  "COMMIT2_ITER1_REQUEST_CHANGES_ITER2_INFLIGHT_2026_06_21": "Commit-2 V2 (wf w9m7k2j1w) split build SUCCEEDED (beat the timeout; smoke all-green: _CLAIM_WORKERS rebind 6->12 PROVEN, storm restore 14>9 sections, faithfulness clean). But Codex gate iter-1/5 = REQUEST_CHANGES, 0 P0, 3 P1, 1 P2 -- all REAL: P1-1 PG_DISTILL_MICROBATCH_SIZE is NOT parallelism (batches sources per distill MAP call -> changes the prompt envelope + WHICH findings = faithfulness-adjacent) -> REMOVE from the parallelism slate. P1-2 storm checkpoint VIOLATES its DATA-ONLY contract: write_storm_outline_checkpoint model_dump()s the WHOLE StormOutlineSection incl evidence_summary+perspectives = STORM-AUTHORED PROSE -> persist ONLY scaffold fields {title,description,search_keywords,order}, harness assert prose absent. P1-3 load_storm_outline_checkpoint silently returns [] on a PRESENT-but-malformed file (_payload.get('storm_outline',[])) -> reproduces the resume no-op it prevents -> fail-LOUD on present-but-malformed, None only if ABSENT. P2 the PG_MAX_PARALLEL_SECTIONS 'inert' comment is STALE -- it IS consumed at run_honest_sweep_r3.py:8806 (max_parallel_sections kwarg); the call-time OVERRIDE is PG_PARALLEL_SECTIONS (multi_section_generator.py:7242) -> fix comment + add PG_PARALLEL_SECTIONS=6. ITER-2 fix wf wvsym7j2p IN FLIGHT (split build: A=run_gate_b remove-microbatch+section-knob, B=run_honest_sweep storm scaffold-only-persist + fail-loud-restore + harness) -> smoke -> Codex re-gate iter 2/5. ON APPROVE commit (run_gate_b.py + run_honest_sweep_r3.py + scripts/iarch_beatboth008_commit2_replay_harness.py; verify ONLY those staged + git show --name-only matches) ref #1285 -> P5 preflight -> P6. Note the codex_diff_audit_commit2.txt is overwritten each gate (trust the workflow RESULT). Codex caught 6 real issues across the #1285 gate rounds (3 model-completeness P1s + 3 commit-2 P1s) + the smoke caught the a04cbf23 omission -- the two-audit discipline is doing its job.",
  "COMMIT2_ITER3_INFLIGHT_2026_06_21": "Commit-2 iter-2 (wf wvsym7j2p) closed P1-1 (microbatch removed) + P1-2 (storm checkpoint scaffold-only no-prose) + P2 (PG_PARALLEL_SECTIONS=6) -- smoke all-green -- but Codex iter-2/5 = REQUEST_CHANGES on a CONTINUING P1-3 (verified vs source): load_storm_outline_checkpoint relied on StormOutlineSection(**d) to raise, but storm_interviews.py:380 COERCES title=None->'' so storm_outline:[{}] loads as a BLANK-TITLE section that silently no-ops the scaffold builder = the exact resume no-op P1-3 prevents. ITER-3 fix wf w8j767mv5 IN FLIGHT (single small build, run_honest_sweep_r3.py loader + harness): explicit per-section validation (require LIST + per-section DICT + NONBLANK title BEFORE the lenient constructor; raise on storm_outline:[{}]/non-list/non-dict-section; absent->None, empty-valid->[], valid-N>9->N>9) + 3 new harness raise-cases -> smoke -> Codex re-gate iter 3/5. ON APPROVE commit (run_gate_b.py + run_honest_sweep_r3.py + scripts/iarch_beatboth008_commit2_replay_harness.py; verify ONLY those staged + git show --name-only matches) ref #1285 -> P5 -> P6. Codex has now caught 7 real issues across #1285 (3 model + 4 commit-2) -- the gate is genuinely hardening the resume-checkpoint correctness; converging (iter 3/5).",
  "P6_FRESH_RUN_LAUNCHED_2026_06_21": "#1285 build COMPLETE + committed (a04cbf23 + 90e68f32 + fcbd55cc, all Codex-APPROVE, 7 real issues caught/fixed). OFFLINE config proof PASSED (no spend): after the slate -> PG_GENERATOR_MODEL=PG_MIRROR_MODEL=z-ai/glm-5.2, _CLAIM_WORKERS=12 (rebind works), PG_PARALLEL_VERIFY=24, PG_PARALLEL_SECTIONS=6, PG_STORM_ENABLED_IN_BENCHMARK=1 + PG_STORM_OUTLINE_SECTIONS=1 (BOTH storm flags on -> fresh run WILL fire STORM), reasoning=xhigh; verify_lock --consistency exit0. P6 DECISIVE FRESH RUN LAUNCHED (no --resume): PID 61722, nohup, log=outputs/p6_fresh_glm52/run.log, out-root=outputs/p6_fresh_glm52, PG_AUTHORIZED_SWEEP_APPROVAL=1, PG_MAX_COST_PER_RUN=25 cap. Launch CONFIRMED LIVE: '03:39:18 OpenRouter client initialized: model=z-ai/glm-5.2' + 'Concurrency semaphore max=8' (all-GLM-5.2 + parallelism active, clean start). MONITOR PLAN (forensic each tick, feedback_monitor_means_line_by_line_forensic): read run.log + four_role_compute_progress.json; the P5 KEYSTONE check at ~20-30min = grep '[multi_section] STORM-outline section scaffold: N sections' N>9 (the breadth-machinery-fires proof on a FRESH run -- the whole point); report DECOMPOSED cited-source breadth estimate each tick; watch D8 done/total cadence (want ~12-worker bursts not 1/3-5s -- the D8_COMPLETION_BLOCKER), glm/minimax latency, cost vs $25. IF STORM<N>9 (fell to legacy V30-P2) OR D8 serial OR dead-on-arrival fix OR error_* -> KILL (taskkill PID 61722) + that is the next bug, fix FIRST (I-arch-005). ELSE continue to completion -> §-1.1 audit report.md -> benchmark BOTH boards (DeepTRACE pack_deeptrace+Venkit populate_scores ; DRB-II run_evaluation.py) -> summarize problems -> research fixes -> hamster. Providers healthy (Friendli glm-5.2 3.3s). run is harness-UNtracked (nohup) -> poll via run.log each loop tick + the pid.",
