  "HEAD_2026_06_20": "71535441 — D8 complete + parity-green (151 tests). 8 commits today: plan-pin, fetch-shell, PR-c+#1279+F1-1-producer, relevance gate, stale-test, abstractive writer, D8 transport, D8 parity-fix.",
  "f1_1284_status": "NOT BUILT. The F1-2 guard module + _join_verified_clauses + F1-3 caller wiring + PG_SYNTHESIS_MULTICITED flag DO NOT EXIST (forensically verified 2026-06-20). Every build attempt (4x: original, 2 in fan-out, split-code) hit the API stream-idle timeout; each partial was reverted, so nothing landed. The earlier \"completed\" markers were FALSE. Only the F1-1 PRODUCER (compose_multicited_sentence, default-OFF, NO caller) is committed (9df1c5ee #1278). DESIGN is Codex-APPROVED iter-3 (state/beatboth_campaign/F1_WIRING_DESIGN.md). NEXT (fresh session, fresh context): build F1-2/F1-2b/F1-3 from the approved design in TINY steps or by hand (the P0 distinct-origin guard MUST be Codex-diff-gated, not self-approved), then harness, then commit.",
  "P6_V1_CRASH_DOCLING_FIX_V2_RELAUNCH_2026_06_21": {
    "status": "P6 v1 CRASHED in retrieval (native segfault), root-caused + fixed (faithfulness-neutral, config-only), v2 relaunched fresh and HEALTHY past preflight+STORM",
    "v1_crash": {
