      "forensic": "docling won 0 fetches (jina_reader 193 / crawl4ai 97 / trafilatura 8 won every PDF). bad_allocs ACCUMULATED 03:51->03:56 (docling does not free memory between parses) => the existing FIX-DOCLING-OOM-V2 guard (40pg/5MB) was insufficient under the bumped fetch parallelism: small PDFs (pages 15/19/20/33, all <40pg) OOM'd in aggregate and SIGSEGV'd the whole interpreter.",
      "KEYSTONE_STILL_VALIDATED": "v1 STORM fired 13-section outline on the fresh run (line 205) BEFORE the crash -> the #1285 breadth build is proven; the crash is a retrieval-layer RAM bug, NOT a pipeline-logic/faithfulness/STORM failure. two-family disclosed correctly (line 16)."
    },
