  "P6_RUN_COMPLETE_ABORT_EXCESSIVE_GAP_0651": {
    "MILESTONE": "P6 v2 RUN COMPLETE @06:51 (PID dead, report.md+manifest written; trailing 0x80000003 is post-write teardown crash, harmless). docling-fix held all run (bad_alloc=0). cost=$8.21 (<$25). corpus=829 (T1 25%), agentic fired 800 urls, STORM fired 12 outline sections.",
    "OUTCOME": "status=abort_excessive_gap. report.md=3324 bytes (ABORT VERDICT ARTIFACT, not shippable content).",
    "ROOT_CAUSE_chokepoint_A": "ALL 12 STORM sections drafted via 'verified-compose PRIMARY' (2000-3500 chars, 15-25 baskets each) BUT final verdict = verified=0 dropped=0 gap_stub=True for every one. The dropped=0 signature = drafted sentences NEVER entered strict_verify -> draft discarded, section defaults to gap_stub. The I-arch-011 #1268 verified-compose PRIMARY layer DRAFTS but does NOT WIRE drafts into strict_verify accounting. Classic 'fired-in-slate-not-output / committed != wired'.",
    "CONTRAST_working_paths": "3 contract outline sections (Foundational_Theory/Empirical_Displacement/Generative_AI_Evidence) verified 28/12/12 via their path; Corroborated Weighted Findings verified 1300 via FIX-K verified-span render. Only the verified-compose PRIMARY path (12 STORM sections) is broken.",
    "chokepoint_B_symptom": "4/16=25% < PG_MIN_VERIFIED_SECTION_FRACTION=0.40 floor -> abort_excessive_gap discards 1352 verified sentences (incl 1300-sentence 681-source findings) into a 3KB stub. Violates operator always-release directive. BUT this is a SYMPTOM of A: fix A -> 12 STORM sections verify -> floor clears -> ships.",
    "breadth_proven": "the breadth machinery WORKS (829 corpus, 728 baskets, 681 SUPPORTS, 1300 verified sentences in findings). The defect is purely the verified-compose PRIMARY -> strict_verify wiring for topical STORM sections.",
    "benchmark_blocked": "can't score DeepTRACE/DRB-II on a 3KB abort stub (would score ~0). Must fix chokepoint A + re-run first.",
    "next": "advisor -> GH issue -> grep verified_compose.py + multi_section_generator.py strict_verify handoff -> Claude Codex Workflow fix + fail-loud replay harness (§-1.4) -> re-run."
  },
  "P6_ROOTCAUSE_FINAL_verified_compose_measurement_stub": {
    "CONFIRMED_ROOT_CAUSE": "verified-compose PRIMARY (multi_section_generator.py:3910, gated PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE) is a DELIBERATE breadth-MEASUREMENT stub. Code comment: 'The stub writer (returns \"\") forces the deterministic verbatim K-span per basket for the breadth MEASUREMENT -- NO LLM, no spend; the production per-basket generator-role writer is finalized AFTER the measurement confirms breadth.' The slate run_gate_b.py:955 sets PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE=1, routing 12 STORM sections through this stub in a PRODUCTION run -> stub yields thin/empty draft -> 0 verified -> gap_stub -> 25%<40% -> abort_excessive_gap. Textbook committed!=wired.",
    "FIX-K_is_proven": "the Corroborated Weighted Findings section (1300 verified) uses FIX-K _build_verified_span_draft(section.ev_ids,...) gated on _evsr (line 3896), NOT PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE. Deterministic verbatim-span render that grounds. PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE=0 does NOT disable FIX-K (advisor blast-radius check: SAFE).",
    "FIX_PLAN": [
      "1. GH issue FIRST (§-1.2).",
      "2. OFFLINE PROBE TEST (advisor, §-1.4 replay-harness): load ONE STORM section's baskets+evidence_pool from postgen_checkpoint.json, run verified-compose PRIMARY stub -> _rewrite_draft_with_spans -> strict_verify, READ output. If '[insufficient verified evidence]' disclosures => baskets dont ground => NO writer fixes it, faithfulness NOT relaxed, different fix. If groundable-but-thin => writer bug => FIX-K-style fix works.",
      "3. FIX (if groundable): wire the verbatim-K-span-per-basket logic (FIX-K _build_verified_span_draft style) into verified-compose PRIMARY replacing the measurement stub, so topical sections produce groundable verbatim spans through UNCHANGED strict_verify (faithfulness untouched). + FAIL-CLOSED assertion: slate must NOT route through verified-compose with a stub/no-composer in production (advisor: the committed!=wired guard).",
      "4. REPLAY-HARNESS validate on banked corpus (STORM section flips gap_stub->verified>0), minutes not 2.5h.",
      "5. Codex gate (5-iter cap).",
      "6. Re-run FRESH -> shippable report -> §-1.1 audit -> score DeepTRACE + DRB-II."
    ],
    "faithfulness_boundary": "BOTH options change only the WRITER, not the verify gate. Fix must make GENUINELY-grounded content flow, NOT relax strict_verify. State as non-goal in Codex brief.",
    "audit_deliverable": "outputs/p6_fresh_glm52_v2/CLAUDE_AUDIT.md written (full §-1.1).",
    "next": "GH issue -> offline probe test (the decisive gate before any fix)."
  },
  "P6_FIX_PROBE_prc_harness_passes_0713": {
    "PR_C_HARNESS_PASSES": "scripts/iarch011_prc_verified_compose_replay_harness.py exit 0 -- verified-compose PRIMARY LOGIC is SOUND: with baskets carrying verified spans it composes verified prose, verbatim-K-span fallback fires (c1), faithful compose passes strict_verify (c2), foreign-cite rejected (c3). So the compose ENGINE works; the P6 0-verified means the REAL STORM-section baskets didn't ground through the stub writer -> insufficient-evidence disclosures -> stripped -> 0/0.",
    "two_proven_writers_on_this_corpus": "_call_section (the 3 contract sections verified 28/12/12) AND FIX-K _build_verified_span_draft via _evsr (findings 1300 verified, INDEPENDENT of PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE -- confirmed line 3896 checked before the elif). The verified-compose PRIMARY stub is the ONLY broken writer.",
    "fix_fork": {
      "A_pg_verified_compose_0": "route the 12 STORM topical sections to _call_section (proven, readable LLM prose) by disabling PG_VERIFIED_COMPOSE in the slate. findings keeps FIX-K. simplest, faithfulness-neutral, lowest-risk; reverts the (never-finalized) verified-compose-per-section breadth feature.",
