  "FORENSIC_WORKFLOW_VERDICT_whe442ry9": {
    "verdict": "SOUND-SO-FAR with 2 P1 watch-items, NOT yet certifiable. 4 independent deep-reads (retrieval/STORM, tool+retrieval traces, corpus/credibility, gen-start/monitor) CONVERGE: pipeline WEIGHTS+KEEPS sources (no filter/cap), faithfulness gates (strict_verify/4-role D8/fail-closed entailment) INTACT + not relaxed. NO fabrication, NO mis-attribution, NO silent-drop found. Genuine (each agent cited distinct mechanical evidence: 294/294 down-weight ledger, 0-of-579 honest-drop, verbatim span checks, model refusing to invent Frey-Osborne 47%); 2 agents refused to certify what they couldn't see.",
    "P1_B1_fabrication_seed": "corpus_snapshot.json evidence_id 'acemoglu_restrepo_robots_jobs' (v30_frame_row=True): a T1 structured-frame HERO row has direct_quote LENGTH 0 (empty grounding span) but a populated empirical statement ('Robots and Jobs: Evidence from US Labor Markets'), NO full-text backup in pool. Empty-span T1 frame claim = fabrication-seed: if the generator emits it, strict_verify has no span to check. ACTION: at the OUTPUT §-1.1 audit, check if this source is CITED in report.md; if cited, the sentence MUST be verbatim-grounded or dropped. strict_verify is the backstop (empty-span can't ground) -- verify the engine catches it.",
    "P1_B2_not_rendered": "run not complete (no report.md/manifest/verdict). OUTPUT (final breadth, surviving sections, tail-drop resurfacing) unverifiable until completion. Project rule committed/green/in-slate != fired-in-output -> cannot certify from snapshot. ACTION: full §-1.1 line-by-line OUTPUT audit on report.md at completion.",
    "P2_B3_coverage_vs_instruction": "question demands 'high-quality English-language journal articles' but that exact venue class (OUP/QJE, AEA/AER/JEP, Science, Elsevier, Wiley, JSTOR) DOMINATES the 139 sources down-weighted to 0.050 (publisher paywalls defeat the fetcher). Honestly disclosed, partly rescued by OA mirrors (repec/nber/mit/PMC bring Autor2015, Acemoglu-Restrepo in at full text), but residual coverage loss not fully quantifiable; corpus reaching generation has weighted_mean credibility 0.33 / UNKNOWN 35%. The paywall-fetch (Zyte) lever needs improvement for journal-heavy questions.",
    "P2_B4_topical_drift": "~30+ off-topic sources (computational neuroscience, deep-learning-as-brain-model, medical-AI-diagnosis, O*NET taxonomy) entered the corpus KEPT not gated, for an AI-labor-market review. Pre-fetch relevance gate culled clinical-epi noise but DID NOT fire on these -> gate-coverage gap (not a missing gate). Corpus-precision concern.",
    "P2_two_family": "PG_PERMIT_GENERATOR_EVALUATOR_SAME_FAMILY=1 (both GLM-5.2) disables the §9.1.1 two-family self-bias safeguard -- operator-approved + DISCLOSED, but self-bias risk in the 4-role D8 + credibility judge (same GLM family); carry into the verify/judge OUTPUT audit.",
    "positives": "§-1.3 weight-not-drop CORRECT (139 degraded labeled+down-weighted+KEPT, evidence_selector 0-of-579 honest-drop, BUG-14 keeps 64 below-floor flagged-not-dropped); M-23d short-content-with-HTTP-error guard WORKING (anti-degraded-as-fulltext); OA-mirror routing rescues canonical literature; agentic gap-driven retrieval SOUND (names real gaps, genuine snowball not target-chasing).",
    "carry_to_output_audit": [
      "B1 empty-span acemoglu_restrepo_robots_jobs cited?",
      "B4 do off-topic sources get cited?",
      "two-family self-bias in D8/credibility verdicts",
      "collapsed=0 finding_dedup -> do baskets actually consolidate multi-source?"
    ]
  },
