  "P6_V3_OPERATOR_DIRECTIVE_AUDIT_BENCH_FIX_RESUME_0940": {
    "operator_directive": "3-part: (1) NOW forensically audit + benchmark the current rendered report.md line-by-line vs BOTH scoreboards; (2) keep the current local run (PID 47424) grinding its 5h D8 -- do NOT kill; (3) fix qwen-max_tokens + resume the D8 from postverify_checkpoint on a NEW box (so it finalizes fast).",
    "audit_launched": "§-1.1 forensic audit Workflow wpku1kjjj (run wf_4784e549-921): 4 line-by-line agents over report.md (1587 lines) + synthesis. report uses numeric [182] citations (not raw [#ev:]). EARLY-SEEN issues: line 153 Century-Foundation privacy-boilerplate leak (repeated 4x), line 103 garbled fragment header, B1 'Robots and Jobs JPE 2020' IS cited (line 49) -> audit must verify grounded.",
    "benchmark_paths_confirmed": "DeepTRACE: scripts/dr_benchmark/pack_deeptrace.py + run_deeptrace.py + third_party/answer-engine-eval/Venkit.et.al.2024/populate_scores.py. DRB-II: third_party/DeepResearch-Bench-II/run_evaluation.py. (Both likely need external judge API keys -- GPT-5/Gemini -- check next.)",
    "qwen_fix_scoped": "ROOT CAUSE: qwen3.6-35b-a3b is a REASONING-FIRST model so openrouter_client.py:1921 _apply_completion_cap = model NOT in _REASONING_FIRST_MODELS -> the completion cap is SKIPPED -> max_tokens defaults to full context 262140 -> qwen emits huge reasoning per claim -> 5h D8. judge_adapter.py:67 _DEFAULT_MAX_TOKENS=16 (judge is MEANT to be short). token_limit_resolver clamps 262140->259555 (proactive, prevents the fatal 400 -- so the '42 qwen-400s' was a MISCOUNT of clamp-warning lines, not real 400s). FIX: cap the JUDGE role's max_tokens to a modest value (e.g. 4096-8192: enough reasoning+verdict, not 262K). §9.1.8 'tokens MAX' is for the GENERATOR not the short-verdict judge -- capping the judge is NOT starving. Codex-gate it.",
    "next": "relay audit synthesis when wpku1kjjj lands -> run BOTH benchmarks on report.md (check API-key reqs first) -> build qwen-judge-max_tokens fix + Codex-gate -> check VM availability (vast 423175/ssh8.vast.ai:39556) + deploy+resume D8 there -> summarize -> hamster. Keep PID 47424 ALIVE."
  },
  "P6_V3_AUDIT_VERDICT_DO_NOT_SHIP_1015": {
    "VERDICT": "§-1.1 line-by-line audit (4 readers, full 1587 lines): DO NOT SHIP. The report has a real faithfulness defect but it is NOT fabrication. My earlier '475KB WIN' was PREMATURE -- the line-by-line audit (operator demanded) caught what the surface 'all-sections-non-empty' check MISSED.",
    "GOOD_engine_held": "ZERO fabrication (0/~77 sampled claims). Faithfulness/span-grounding engine HELD per-claim. B1 empty-span seed did NOT bite (ref [10] acemoglu_restrepo_robots_jobs quote_len=0 grounds ZERO claims; honest gap-disclosure; fail-loud worked). The 2 compose bugs ARE fixed (sections render content, no abort).",
    "BAD_new_P0_defects": [
      "P0 FALSE SELF-CERTIFICATION (crosses into faithfulness): the Abstract/Key-Findings header + Conclusion self-certify 'Each sentence below is a verbatim, span-verified statement' but render scraped Scribd/Facebook/YouTube boilerplate + mid-word garble under that label. The §-1.1 lethal-miss case (blind reader trusts the false label).",
      "P0 SCRAPED-BOILERPLATE LEAK: the 3 body STORM sections are almost entirely raw scraped markdown (Scribd/oauth download links, Brookings nav, YouTube channel blurbs, Facebook 'Like Comment Share' + 'Reviewer 2 Must Be Stopped', bare citation-marker runs [14][15][16]...). Root cause: the verbatim-K-span render ships whatever is in the strongest member's span INCLUDING page chrome; the fetch/clean layer didn't strip boilerplate. The compose-bug fix EXPOSED this (v2 ate the spans=empty=hid it; v3 renders them=junk visible).",
      "P0 UNSUPPORTED STATS shipped as body text: 77% China-jobs (L83), 14% role-share (L99), 26.08%/4867-devs (L105), 40% AI-adoption (L100) -- orphaned scraped fragments, no point-of-use citation."
    ],
    "P1_P2_defects": "P1 garbled header (L103 two run-together H1 fragments); P1 EXTREME REPETITION (same fact restated 10-15x: Autor ~14x L43, 5172-agents ~11x L59) because fact_dedup was SKIPPED (the COT-1 qwen-truncation bug); P2 think-tank/news stats cited where the question demands ONLY journal articles (B3 coverage-vs-instruction confirmed).",
    "verdict_totals": "sampled ~77 claims: VERIFIED 18, PARTIAL 21, UNSUPPORTED 30, FABRICATED 0. All 4 readers independently returned REJECT/not-publication-grade.",
    "ROOT_CAUSES_to_fix": "the engine is intact; BROKEN layers: (1) fetch/clean boilerplate-strip (scraped chrome in evidence spans), (2) the verbatim-span render dumping chrome instead of synthesized prose (the ABSTRACTIVE WRITER PG_ABSTRACTIVE_WRITER is OFF -> the no-LLM stub dumps raw spans), (3) fact_dedup (qwen COT-1 truncation -> repetition), (4) the false 'span-verified' self-certification label, (5) point-of-use source-gating (unsupported stats + think-tank sources).",
    "benchmark_implication": "scoring THIS report = a low/junk baseline (boilerplate tanks DeepTRACE citation-accuracy + DRB-II coverage). Useful as a BASELINE but not representative of the pipeline's potential. Real path: fix the boilerplate/dedup/abstractive-writer/self-cert layers -> re-run -> benchmark clean.",
