[7m[0m      # I-wire-014 (#1327): snap the head cut back to the last word boundary at/before[0m
[7m[0m      # ``head_chars`` so the stored span NEVER ends mid-word ("usand workers"). The[0m
[7m[0m      # integer ``head_chars`` cap below (the ``e > head_chars`` window filter) is[0m
[7m[0m      # unchanged; only the emitted head STRING is trimmed to a whole word. ``head``[0m
